title: barbecue
directions: Cook roast slowly in small amount of water until very tender. Remove from heat.
When slightly cool, remove bone and fat.
Cut into small pieces.
Return to heat.
Add other ingredients; cook until meat is stringy, stirring often.
Delicious served on toasted hamburger buns.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put stick of margarine in pan and put in oven.
Let melt.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add milk and stir good.
Put mixture into pan with margarine; stir.
Sprinkle fruit on top.
Stir around a little. Put other cup of sugar on top.
Sprinkle all around.
Cook until golden brown.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the first 7 ingredients to include soda, pulp, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and beaten egg.
Blend thoroughly and gradually add flour.
Slowly add milk while stirring.
Finally, add melted margarine and pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Bone, skin and cut each breast in half about 1 hour before serving.
Pound each chicken breast half to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Place bread crumbs in pie plate.
Moisten chicken pieces with water, then dip into bread crumbs to coat evenly.

title: glazed carrots and onions
directions: Cook carrots until done.

title: corn and cheese pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp mold spread
directions: Combine ingredients in order of listing.
Fold together and spoon into an oiled 3 1/2 cup mold. Refrigerate until set.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: zucchini and carrots
directions: Use a large frying pan or wok. Add oil and garlic to a hot pan.
Then add carrots. Saute or stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add zucchini. Toss about for 3 minutes.
Add the lemon juice and wine. Toss about and remove from heat.
Serve immediately.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer in order listed, using about 1/2 of each ingredient in the first round and the remainder of each ingredient in the second round of layers, always beginning with cake crumbs and ending
with
coconut.
Chill
several hours or overnight before serving.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, syrup, vanilla, Quik and nuts.
Set aside, then mix sugar, butter, milk and peanut butter.
Boil about 2 minutes. Pour second mixture over first mixture.
Mix well and put on cookie sheet.
Let set for about 2 hours.

title: grandma elsie's lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend egg yolks, cornstarch, salt, sugar, rind from 2 lemons and juice.
Add to 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir until thick. Remove from heat and add margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites, adding sugar and vanilla to taste.
Pile on top of pie and place in 350° oven until meringue is brown.

title: gazpacho
directions: Soak bread in a bowl with enough water until it is reduced to a thick mush.

Blend the juice, one pepper, one cucumber, one onion, bread, olive oil and vinegar in a blender in stages. Pour each blender batch into a large bowl and add salt to taste. Refrigerate for several hours.
Chop up the remaining pepper, cucumber and onion and refrigerate until you are ready to serve the gazpacho.
Serve ice cold and garnish with the chopped up vegetables and croutons.

title: pecan squash casserole
directions: Blanch corn-on-the-cob, then cool in ice water.
Wrap each ear separately in foil; store in freezer.
To cook, drop wrapped corn into pot of boiling water and return to boil.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve in foil.
Keeps very moist.

title: hot brandied fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Combine juices.
Stir well and set aside 1 cup of juice mixture.
Melt butter.
Add sugar, stirring until smooth. Add reserved 1 cup of juice, brandy and spices.
Stir until well blended.

title: broccoli and cauliflower with cheese sauce(this is a rich dish, but oh, so good.)
directions: Leave cauliflower head whole.
Wash and parboil for 10 minutes.
Do the same with the broccoli.
Place cauliflower in a large casserole dish and spread broccoli around it.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix well, all except Cool Whip.
When ready to serve, add Cool Whip.
Mix well.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cut tomatoes up and chop peppers and onions.
Add remaining ingredients in large cooking pot.
Cook fast for 30 minutes.
Then cook on medium-low for 1 1/2 hours or until thick.

title: garden casserole
directions: Cut red pepper in strips.
Saute first 3 ingredients in butter until crisp-tender.
Add flour.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: all you can eat vegetable stew
directions: Dissolve the bouillon in water in a big pot.
Add tomatoes, then the fresh vegetables in succession.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add the frozen, then the canned beans.
Simmer for an hour or so, until soup thickens and the flavors blend.
Adjust salt to taste.

title: martha washington's chocolates
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once.
Roll into small balls and freeze or refrigerate until icy cold.
Melt 1/4 package Gulf wax and drop in 4 squares unsweetened chocolate.
Melt while stirring constantly.
Let cool a bit.
Dip the refrigerated mixture into the chocolate mixture by placing on skewer and immersing in chocolate.
(May have to dip twice to completely cover with chocolate if chocolate is too hot.)
Place on waxed paper.
Keep airtight container.
Refrigerate.

title: spiced bundt cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pizzeola
directions: Put onions on bottom of pan; then add tomatoes, salt, pepper, cheese and steak.
Repeat.
Add water if it gets dry after cooking for a while.
May be baked, covered or uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cut meat in bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 3 1/2 hours. Serve over noodles, rice or potatoes.
(Freeze several meals.)

title: fruited cranberry cole slaw
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar.
Moisten cabbage with orange juice. Add sugared cranberries, celery, green pepper and grapes to cabbage.
Toss lightly with mayonnaise.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta a'oilia sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, brown garlic and celery in oil.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Pour over cooked pasta.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition.
Add bananas and sifted dry ingredients. Blend only enough to moisten flour.
Add nuts and raisins and pour into oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: zucchini(microwave)
directions: Place zucchini, onion and butter in a 1-quart casserole. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes.
(Do not cook them soft, crunchy is always better.) Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Toss gently.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in mixture.
Brown on all sides in hot shortening.
Remove chicken.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onions until translucent.
Add tomatoes and English peas.
Salt to taste.
Add chicken and cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: orange puffs
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in cupcake tins in
moderate oven.

title: angel food pie(m. r. penwell)
directions: Bring pineapple, water, sugar and salt to boil in a double boiler.
Mix the cornstarch in cold water.
Add to above mixture. Cook until thick.
Cool and put in pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream and nuts.
Let stand in icebox several hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the lard, sugars and peanut butter together.
Add egg and
mix.
Add flour and soda sifted together.
Roll small balls of	dough
in
hand
(teaspoonful).
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press
flat
with	tines of a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 50 to 60 small cookies.

title: easter egg nests
directions: Over low heat, melt margarine.
Add marshmallows, stirring occasionally until melted smooth.
Add peanut butter and again stir until melted smooth.
Stir in noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts; cut in small pieces.
Melt butter; add butter to dressing.
Add broth from chicken, if you feel dressing is too dry.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place peeled and cut carrots in 1-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix flour
and
salt
together
in a large bowl or pan. Add half
the
shortening.
Cut
in until mixture is like fine meal. Cut
in remaining shortening until size of a large pea. Put mix in
a large plastic container.
Store in a dry place. Do
not refrigerate.
Makes
enough
for about 12 large pies. Keeps for months.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Sift and measure dry ingredients.
Set aside. Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Add milk and dry ingredients alternately, mixing after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Top with canned peaches (no juice) and bake until browned well at 350°.

title: green chili rice
directions: Mix rice and sour cream. Spread 1/2 of this mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle 1/2 of the Jack cheese over the top. Add the diced chilies, then cover with the remaining Jack cheese. Add remaining rice. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese and top with the Cheddar cheese. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until heated through. This dish makes a great accompaniment for roast beef.

title: broccoli burritos
directions: Wrap
tortillas
tightly in aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 15	minutes.
Combine broccoli, cheese, tomato and onion; spoon mixture evenly in center of each tortilla.	Roll up each tortilla; place
seam
side down in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking
dish.
Top	with tomato sauce.
Cover dish and bake at 350°
for
minutes.
Spread
sour cream over top; garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Add pineapple to cheese; mix pepper, onion and salt into mixture.
Add half of nuts.
Chill in refrigerator then form into 2 balls.
Cover with remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and keep in refrigerator.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add powdered sugar and egg yolks. Mix well by hand.
Take 1/2 of angel food cake and break it up in small pieces in bottom of a large bowl.
Pour half of the butter mixture over cake.
Crunch 2 Butterfinger candy bars or 1 1/2 bars. Sprinkle over mixture.
Then pinch the remaining half of the cake on candy bars.
Pour the other half of the mixture on cake.
Top with 1 1/2 more Butterfinger candy bars.
Refrigerate for a while before serving.

title: incredible edibles
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Press into greased 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over top.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Make sauce of remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Top with Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes or a little longer at 350°.

title: fruit bars
directions: Melt butter; mix with eggs.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and salt, then add to egg mixture.
Mix fruit and nuts; add to batter.
Spread in two 9-inch square baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars and wrap.

title: chicken apricot delight
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, meat side up.
Mix apricot jelly, onion soup mix and Russian dressing.
Baste chicken with mixture and bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken is done.
Keep basting chicken while baking.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Slice the Velveeta and layer slices over broccoli.
Slice margarine and layer slices over broccoli and cheese.
Pour cream of chicken soup over top and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini noodles according to package directions. Drain. Add veggies. Mix with Italian dressing. Mix well. Sprinkle with Feta cheese.

title: ginny's macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Boil 3 cups macaroni until half done; drain.
Place half in baking dish.
Cut up 1 package cheese over macaroni and 1/2 margarine.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: With one cup of hot water, add all ingredients into bowl. Chill in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or until ready to eat.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onions together.
Add to the remaining ingredients.
Top with bread cubes.
Bake at 350° until bread cubes are toasted, approximately 30 minutes.

title: coca-cola barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in skillet.
Cover with barbecue sauce and Coca-Cola.
Cook on top of stove until sauce is thickened and chicken is done.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in quart jar; cover tightly and shake well to blend.
Store remainder, covered, in refrigerator for future use.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine until tender; drain.
Add melted butter, cream, salt and pepper.
Toss until well blended.
Add Parmesan cheese and mix.
Serve hot.

title: cranberry-apple casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and 2 tablespoons flour.
Add sugar and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir well.
Spoon over the fruit mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave on High for 12 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Slice and cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mounds candy bar
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Press into a long Pyrex dish and let chill overnight in refrigerator.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler over low heat.
Stir frequently to blend. Cut coconut mixture into squares and using toothpicks, dip into chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pineapple marshmallow dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in double boiler.
Stir until all marshmallows are melted.
Let cool in refrigerator until a little thick.
Whip 1 pint of whipping cream.
Add to marshmallow mixture. Fold in well drained pineapple.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumb crust.
Pour marshmallow mixture on top. Let stand in refrigerator for several hours.
May be made the night before.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of about a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together; pour on top of margarine.
Then pour in peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add enough mayonnaise to make creamy consistency.
Add crab to mixture.
Top with cocktail sauce and chill.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil and beat.
Mix spices and salt with flour.
Mix milk and prunes; add soda.
Add liquid to egg, sugar and oil mixture.
Add flour mixture and pecans.
Mix well. Bake in Bundt pan 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pepper rings
directions: Boil together oil, water and vinegar.
Slice peppers into rings into pint jars.
Place 1 clove garlic in jar.
Fill with peppers.
Add salt and oregano.
Add boiling liquid and seal.
Do a 5-minute hot water bath.

title: dark rye bread
directions: Stir honey into water until dissolved.
Sprinkle yeast over water to soften.
Stir together in large bowl next 6 ingredients. Beat in molasses.
Allow to stand 10 minutes.
Add whole wheat flour and beat.
Add enough white flour to make a stiff dough.

title: jamaican rice & peas
directions: Grate coconut and using the quart of hot water, express the milk by adding two cups of water at a time and squeezing the milk through a sieve after each addition. Place beans in a saucepan with the coconut milk and add the clove of garlic, slightly bruised. Cook until beans are tender, but not overcooked.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise and Miracle Whip; spread over veggies.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt cheeses over low heat.
Add crab meat.
Pour into a serving bowl.
Serve with Triscuits or crackers.
Serves 2 cups.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir together and add apples and nuts last.
Mix well.
Put cake in 9 inch tube pan in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kelly's texas dip
directions: Brown sausage and beef; drain.
Add onion and pepper and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cheese, Ro-Tel, jalapenos, soup; heat and blend.
Serve hot with chips on side.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: mary anne's armenian rice
directions: Chop the onion, green pepper and celery. Saute in the oil until tender. Add the mushrooms. Cover and simmer a few minutes. Wash the rice.
Put in a 2-quart casserole and add the thyme, salt, pepper, salt, beef consomme and water.
Add the sauteed onion, pepper, celery and mushrooms to casserole. Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Stir after first 1/2 hour. Remove cover the last 10 minutes. Should be dry, not soupy. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pickled pigs feet
directions: Wash pigs feet.
Boil until meat will slip from bone.
Drain. Place meat in bowl.
Combine vinegar, cloves, salt, pepper, bay leaf and onion.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add 2 cups broth in which the pigs feet were cooked.
Strain.
Pour over pigs feet.
Let stand 3 days.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Well grease a 9 x 9-inch pan and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, add sugar and water.
Place on medium heat, stirring constantly.
When it begins a rolling boil, time for 2 1/2 minutes, reducing heat to simmer.
After the allotted time, remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme, then the peanut butter.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: strawberry frozen delight
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar. Blend strawberries and pineapple into creamed mixture.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Pour into pan or cupcake paper or anything pretty and freeze.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Grind nuts and chop fruits fine; mix.
Bake in 250° oven for 3 hours.

title: chicken mandarin
directions: Cut chicken and green pepper into 1/2-inch wide strips; bias-slice green onions.
In wok, electric skillet or large skillet, quick cook and stir chicken strips over medium-high heat in hot oil until browned.
Add green pepper strips, sliced onion and chicken broth.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover. Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain Mandarin oranges, brown sugar, soy sauce and vinegar; slowly blend into cornstarch and ginger.
Add brown sugar mixture to chicken mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in Mandarin oranges; cover and heat through.
Serve chicken mixture over hot cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: no-peak stew(for a crock-pot)
directions: The quantities you use will depend upon your family.
Mix 1 cup water with 3 tablespoons beef soup base starter and 3 tablespoons flour.
Mix and pour over the meat and veggies in the crock-pot.
Stir together and cover with lid.
Cook all day on low.
When you come from work, your dinner is ready.
Add a salad and bread and you're all set.

title: microwave mushroom burgers
directions: Place all ingredients in medium bowl; mix well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Line micro-safe plate with paper towels.
Place patties on top.
Cover with another paper towel.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Turn patties over.
Microwave second side for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Add chicken; marinate for 2 hours or more.
Stir well.
Dip pieces into hot oil; deep fry until browned.

title: creamed peas
directions: Gently fold all ingredients and heat thoroughly, but do not overcook.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well.
Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Drain.
In iron skillet, layer bottom with 1/2 of corn meal mixture.
Top with ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Add jalapeno peppers, and top with shredded cheese.
Add remaining corn meal mixture and bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add 1 teaspoon of mustard and salt. Next, add meat and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Mix cake mix with 2 eggs and butter.
Pour into pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over first layer and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: west meets east soup mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the beans.
Mix to distribute evenly.
Divide bean mixture equally among 12 pint plastic bags or other containers; each should contain about 1 3/4 cups mixed dried beans.

title: indian rice
directions: In a heavy saucepan with a tight fitting lid, melt 1 tablespoon of butter and add onions.
Cook, stirring until wilted. Add rice and cook, stirring about 30 seconds.
Add broth, raisins, lemon, bay leaf, saffron, Tabasco, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Simmer over low heat for 17 minutes.
Uncover and remove bay leaf.
Add remaining butter and stir to fluff the rice well.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: rock road cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Melt 1/2 cup of the chocolate chips and butter over low heat; cool. Mix remaining chocolate chips, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, nuts and chocolate mixture. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press marshmallows into center of each. Bake for 8 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: candied squash rings
directions: Cut squash crosswise in 1-inch slices; discard seeds and ends. Season.
Arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turkey chow mein
directions: Cook celery, onion and mushrooms in oil until crisp and tender, stirring often. Add 2 cans of chicken broth, can of water, soy sauce, meat and bean sprouts. Simmer about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cook vegetables.
Drain macaroni and add vegetables, artichokes and olives.
Mix with salad dressing. Refrigerate.

title: garden dip
directions: In small bowl mash cottage cheese with fork.
Add onion, carrots, green pepper, salt and garlic; beat until fairly smooth. Stir in yogurt.
Cover; chill several hours.
Serve as dip with raw vegetables such as broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, etc.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until fork-tender.
Refrigerate overnight.
Grate potatoes, no need to peel them, the skins will fall off.
Saute the green onions in the melted margarine, just until soft.
Add all ingredients to potatoes.
Mix gently but thoroughly and put in a large baking dish.
Top with more grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mocha icebox cake
directions: Line a spring-form pan around sides and on bottom with split ladyfingers.
Combine in small mixer bowl:
Dream Whip, coffee and cocoa.
Blend in milk following package directions.
Spread 1/3 of whipped mixture over ladyfingers.
Top with ladyfingers.
Spread with second 1/3 of whipped mixture.
Top with ladyfingers, then the remaining whipped mixture.
Cover loosely.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hawaiian hasty pudding
directions: Layer the pineapple, coconut and cake mix in the order given in a long pan.
Sprinkle the chopped pecans and butter slices over the cake mix.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: dream cupcakes
directions: Cream together well cake mix, cream cheese, sugar and salt. Combine chocolate chips and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon in center of cupcakes, then bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Mix the two dressings. Fold in the rest of the ingredients.

title: decadent brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to butter mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chunks and Macadamia nuts.
Spread evenly into a greased 9 X 13 pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove pan to wire rack, cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 24 brownies.

title: zucchini garlic pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl (except nuts). Microwave at Medium (50% power) until chocolate chips are melted, 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch square baking dish. Refrigerate until set.
Makes about 2 pounds.
Eat and enjoy.

title: broccoli-pea casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Arrange broccoli in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, seasonings, cheese, onion and eggs.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Mix onions, pepper, olives and artichoke hearts with cooked Rice-A-Roni.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix mayonnaise, oil from artichokes and curry.
Pour into rice mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add 1 cup crab meat, 1 cup shrimp or 1 cup cooked chicken.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Stir all ingredients except chicken together.
Pour over chicken in skillet.
Cook on top of stove at 250° to 300° with cover on skillet for 45 minutes to an hour.
When half done, turn chicken over.
Cook until tender.

title: holiday beef cheese ball
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl.
When soft, add onion, mayonnaise, sherry and beef.
Mix well.
Add olives; mix carefully.
Chill and form into ball shape.
Ice with sour cream.
Decorate with pimiento strips and parsley.
Decorations are optional.
Can be a spread from a dish.
Good on any snack cracker.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: paintbrush cookies
directions: Mix in a bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the remaining 3 ingredients in another bowl.
Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Mix together the two bowls of ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meats, in oil in a large frypan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add garlic, tomato paste, water, onion, bay leaves, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 1 hour over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: super bowl sloppy joes
directions: Lightly brown beef and separate into chunks as it browns. Pour off excess fat.
Stir in soup and corn and simmer, stirring often, for about 5 minutes.
Add a little water if mixture gets too thick.
Spoon mixture onto buns.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.
tags: condensed chili beef with beans soup

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix refried beans, salsa and taco seasoning and spread on large dish or platter.
Mash avocados; add lemon juice and taco sauce.
Mix together well and spread on top of bean mixture. Spread sour cream on top of that.
Top with lettuce, Cheddar cheese and tomato.
Dip with nachos.

title: cherry spice cake
directions: Mix everything well after dry apple cook mix in.
Cook at 350°.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Chop 6 leaves of cabbage, peeling off outer leaves and quartering.
Run through minimum times so cabbage is uneven.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and allow to marinate.

title: sourdough-sausage quiches
directions: Cut bread slices into 40 rounds, using a 3-inch biscuit cutter. Roll each bread round lightly with a rolling pin. Brush both sides of each round lightly with melted butter. Press into miniature (1 3/4-inch) muffin pans lightly coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crisp and golden.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and oil.
Mix well. Pour into a greased muffin pan. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Yields 12 cornbread muffins.

title: favorite summer dessert
directions: Cut cantaloupe in half and scrape out seeds.
Turn cut side down on plate and chill (preferably overnight).
Remove cantaloupe from refrigerator and turn over, place 1 scoop of ice cream in the center of each half of cantaloupe and serve.

title: sweet potato swirl
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cut into quarters.
Cook potatoes in a large covered saucepan with a small amount of boiling water. Water can be lightly salted.
Cook until potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Drain.
Transfer sweet potatoes into a large mixing bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for about 2 minutes.
Add margarine, salt and pepper to taste.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs and lemon juice in bowl; beat well.
Add flour; beat well.
Add apples and nuts; mix well. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 315° for 1 hour.

title: pea and celery casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add chopped celery and saute a few minutes.
Add thawed peas, mushrooms and sliced water chestnuts.
Add soup and mix together.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle sharp cheese over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain.
Rinse with hot water.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add ingredients, except last four. Simmer 10 minutes, then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well; top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This may be frozen for later.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo, sugar
and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Fold in	pineapple
and	coconut.
In
(9 x 5-inch) pans, bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Fry onion in oleo.
Mix all.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: *Or you can make homemade noodles.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Mix with a fork.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown margarine, onion and rice well in skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add beef bouillon cubes and water.
Bring to a boil. Turn down to simmer. Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream all ingredients together and bake in a greased pan for about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a large pan, cook the meat, onions and carrots slowly until meat is done and onions are transparent (do not brown).
Drain. Add salt and pepper to taste, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce.
Pour mixture into 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with the mashed potatoes which have been prepared according to package directions.
(You may use real mashed potatoes, if you want.) Bake, uncovered, about 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ranch hands breakfast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray both sides of tortillas with Pam cooking spray.
Place 2 tortillas into each of two loaf pans, gently shaping each tortilla to create a bowl.
Heat chili, stir in potatoes and cook until heated.
Divide chili mixture among tortillas.
With back of spoon, make an indentation in each chili mixture.
Break egg into each indentation.
Bake 10 minutes. Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until eggs are done.
Lift out of pans.
Place on plates.
Spoon on tomato and onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with salsa. Serves 4.

title: singing cake*
directions: *Gather your friends around this baking cake and whistle a merry tune along with the cake.

title: cream caramels
directions: Combine ingredients and slowly bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken.
Cook to 254° and pour into 7-inch square pan with 1/2 cup broken nuts scattered over the bottom.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: coffee cake international
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans or a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to mixture alternately with sour cream. Pour batter into pans.
Spread pie filling on top.
Sprinkle Streusel Topping over the filling.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in round pans or 40 to 50 minutes in oblong pan.

title: glazed wings
directions: Prepare grill at least 1/2 hour before cooking, adjusting grid 6 to 8 inches above coals.
Rinse wings and pat dry.
In large bowl, combine vegetable oil, lemon juice and seasoned salt.
Toss chicken pieces in mixture.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Brush onto wings and place wings on grill over white hot coals.
Turn wings and baste with glaze every 8 minutes until golden brown and tender, about 16 to 20 minutes.
Wings are done if juices run clear when pierced with a fork.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Grease a shallow casserole dish.
Mix frozen hash browns with soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add egg, soup, cheese and mayonnaise to squash and onion.
In another bowl, melt margarine, add stuffing and mix well.
Take casserole dish, put 1 layer stuffing mix and then put 1 layer squash mix.
Keep layering until all mixes are gone.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: peach surprise
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
Stir in drained peaches. After jello sets, cut jello in 3-inch squares.
Put into dessert cups and top with whipping cream.
Garnish with orange peelings.

title: aunt thelma's brownies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla, hot water and peanut butter.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Stir in nuts and 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Pour in large greased pan.
Sprinkle the remaining chips.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix together.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
This will keep in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: In microwave bowl, mix chocolate chips and butter.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cut when cool.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: ham casserole
directions: In buttered 9-inch baking dish, sprinkle 1/4-inch layer of cracker crumbs.
Follow with layers of ingredients as listed. Repeat layers to fill dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hungarian goulash(yields 8 servings)
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef or veal in hot shortening. Reduce heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, paprika, salt, pepper, dried thyme and bay leaves.
Add can of tomatoes.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until meat is tender, 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Stir often toward end of cooking.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve at once over hot buttered noodles.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt margarine in aluminum Dutch oven (don't use iron pot; will cause shrimp to darken).
Season shrimp tails generously with Tony's Creole seasoning or salt and pepper.
Add paprika to margarine; saute shrimp tails about 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp and set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add all ingredients.
Salt to taste and place bacon on top.
Bake until tender and all juices are soaked up.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Can be made the day before.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender in rapidly boiling, salted water. (If sides and edges of pan are oiled or buttered, macaroni will not boil over.)
Drain.
In well buttered baking dish, place a layer of macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese cubes.
Sprinkle with few grains salt and pepper (2 or 3 pinches of flour may be added here, if desired).
Dot with butter.
Make another layer in the same order but omit flour.
Make third layer, ending with cheese on top.
Dot with butter and sprinkle paprika over cheese.
Whip eggs in medium size bowl.
Add milk and few grains pepper.
(If salt is added, use sparingly.)
Mix together and pour over macaroni and cheese.
Buttered bread crumbs may be sprinkled on top if desired. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese has melted and is lightly browned.

title: quilter's cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ovenproof dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Stir into creamed mix.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly on top and bake 3 minutes more.
Cool.

title: butterscotch  pecan  cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first five ingredients, mix well. Stir in pecan (the dough will be crumbly).
Roll tablespoonfuls into balls and place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets. bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 2 minutes, remove from pan, to wire racks.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Brown roast on both sides in hot oil in a large Dutch oven. Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onions are tender.
Combine salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour over roast.
Cook over low heat, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 1 hour or until tender. Add potatoes and carrots during last 30 minutes of cooking time. Transfer to serving platter.
Serve with vegetables.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips; set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well. Add to oil, sugar and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients. Add to egg mixture. Add apples, walnuts and cinnamon. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: 100% whole wheat bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Add milk, honey, oil, salt and eggs.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups of flour (I usually put in 3 cups).
Beat 100 strokes by hand or 3 to 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Cover bowl and allow sponge to rise in a warm place until doubled, about 40 to 45 minutes (usually less).
Mix in remaining flour, reserving 1/2 cup for kneading.
Turn out onto floured board and knead thoroughly 8 to 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in oiled bowl; turn dough to oil top.
Cover bowl and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Punch down. Turn out onto board, lightly floured.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks. Makes 2 loaves.

title: ham-asparagus rolls
directions: Blend onion, horseradish, dry mustard and cream cheese. Spread on each ham slice.
Roll up each slice prepared ham around a spear of asparagus.
Secure with toothpick; cut each roll in 1-inch slices.
Arrange as pinwheels on serving dish.

title: barbecued beefburgers
directions: In a large heavy aluminum or steel pot, pour 2 tablespoons salad oil.
Simmer onions, green pepper and celery until transparent.
(Don't brown or fry it.)
Add tomato sauce and everything else, except meat.

title: texas style barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Brush over chicken during last fifteen minutes of grilling.
Yields 3 cups.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Blend cream cheese and 1
sticks
of butter.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick of butter and reserve
it
in a bowl.
Add chopped celery and onion; mix well, then add chicken and black pepper.
Open crescents into a
flat triangle.
Place a tablespoon of filling mixture into the
center,
then fold over the edges to seal mixture.
Dip it
into
the
melted butter, then roll in the bread crumbs.
Place
on an ungreased cookie sheet or large baking pan 1 inch apart.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 24 servings.

title: 5-flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture, alternated with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour in 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: skillet coffee cake
directions: Melt butter; blend with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat. Add vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Line 12-inch iron skillet with aluminum foil; grease lightly.
Pour 1/2 batter in foil lined skillet; sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and chopped nuts.
Add remaining batter, then sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gramma dowsland's brown sugar cookies
directions: Combine egg, shortening and brown sugar, then add 1 cup milk plus 1 teaspoon soda, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 2 to 3 cups flour.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Add 2 tablespoons of Crisco oil to the buttermilk, then add 2 tablespoons cold water. Melt 1 heaping tablespoonful Crisco in biscuit pan. Add enough flour to the buttermilk mixture to make dough that you can handle. Roll out dough on floured board and cut with a biscuit cutter. Bake at 450° on middle rack until well risen, then continue to cook on top rack on broil until golden brown. Makes about 1 dozen biscuits.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal; stir until coated.
Pour into buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Cut into squares.

title: nut roll #1
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows in double boiler; stir until melted.
Combine raisins, coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs, reserving 1 cup for rolling.
Add marshmallow mixture; mix well with hands.
Form into rolls; roll in cracker crumbs.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water slowly, stirring sauce constantly.
Boil over low flame until thickened (5 minutes). Remove from fire and add remaining ingredients.
Beat in 1 egg.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, then sprinkle 1 small box Jell-O in it (any flavor) and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Cream with butter.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in lukewarm water.
Stir and mix well the remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to bake, pinch off balls and put in greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix ingredients well in blender.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup coconut and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Drain kidney and butter beans.
Mix together the beans, hamburger, sugar, catsup, mustard and vinegar and put into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Serve.
Good on hot dogs, too.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts. Beat eggs lightly in large bowl until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple; add dry ingredients.
Stir just until damp.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: winter squash or pumpkin soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk, spinach and grated cheese in a large soup pot.
Cover and simmer for about 25 minutes until vegetables are tender.
If you wish, puree in a blender, 2 cups at a time, and return blended soup to the pot.
Add chopped fresh spinach if you wish.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat until heated through.
Top individual servings with grated cheese.

title: house of lord's burgers
directions: Brown meat; add seasonings.
Stir in soup and pickle relish. Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon over toasted split muffins.
Serve immediately.

title: tea punch
directions: Brew tea bags using package directions.
Add fruit juices and enough water to measure 1 gallon.
Garnish with fresh mint. Yields 1 gallon.

title: shrimp antipasto(makes about 8 cups)
directions: Place shrimp, cheese and olives in large shallow dish.
In small bowl or jar, mix remaining ingredients except salami and pepper.
Pour over shrimp mixture.
Cover; refrigerate 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add salami and pepper; toss.
Drain. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Mix well and bake in Bundt or angel food pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: festive bologna and cheese sandwiches
directions: Take your favorite holiday cookie cutters (metal works the best) and cut out shapes from bread, bologna and cheese.
Make into sandwiches.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Prepare tube pan.
Mix all ingredients, except pineapple and pecans; add these last.
Bake in cold oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Time may vary with ovens.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in 1 cup water in large bowl for several minutes. Mash with fork.
Add ground beef, onion, parsley, cheese, egg, salt and pepper; mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Pour tomato sauce over meat loaf.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and add flour, soda, salt and pineapple.
Bake in large pan at 350° about 40 minutes.
Leave in pan.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in floured tube pan at 350°.
Check between 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet poppy seed bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, poppy seed, baking powder and salt.
Combine eggs, milk, oil, vanilla and almond flavoring together.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until just moistened.
Grease and flour 2 (8 x 4 x 2-inch) loaf pans, or fill muffins 3/4 full.
Bake loaves at 350° for 75 minutes; cover the last 15 minutes.
OR bake muffins at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until tops are brown.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients as listed above on large serving plate. Serve with crackers, chips or Doritos.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook vegetables in broth.
Debone chicken, cut in pieces.
Add soup and cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese melts.

title: bachelor's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble 2 Pop Tarts and place on bottom of baking pan.
Add pie filling.
Top with remaining crumbled Pop Tarts and dot generously with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan and heat on medium-high until clear.
Reduce heat to low; add Jell-O and cook until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Place berries in pie shell and slowly pour Jell-O mixture over berries.
Refrigerate and add whipped topping before serving.
(May use blueberries and/or peaches with appropriate Jell-O.)

title: apple pie
directions: Make a dough out of the Bisquick.
Roll out like a jelly roll. Put cinnamon on the dough.
Cut apples into small pieces; put on dough.
Then roll like a jelly roll; put into a deep dish.
Cut across with a knife.
Then mix butter, water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over apples.
Put in oven at 375°.
Cook until brown.

title: pineapple dream pie
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk with lemon juice. Mix well.
Add pineapple and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill for at least 2
hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from 12 or more huge fresh mushrooms.
Chop for salad or add to stuffing mixture for volume.
Pour melted butter into 7 x 11-inch pan and place mushrooms in one layer.
Mix stuffing ingredients.
If more volume needed, add croutons or chopped mushroom stems.
Stuff tightly into mushrooms.
Put dab of butter in center and arrange croutons around top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) with foil, covering pan tightly.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine, water and cocoa.
In bowl mix remaining ingredients.
Add hot chocolate mix to the bowl.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Mash yams; stir in butter.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar; beat thoroughly.
Add milk, molasses, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; beat until well blended.
Stir mixture into mashed yams.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for about 50 minutes, or until heated throughout.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Wash and slice zucchini, chop onion and garlic and boil in kettle with enough water to cover for 20 minutes until tender. Add tomatoes, chopped chiles and corn.
Cook until corn is tender. Add all the cheese and cook until melted.
Makes a Dutch oven (big kettle) full.
Serve with flour tortillas or crackers.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Distribute ham and cheese evenly in the bottom of the pie shell; set aside.
Mix eggs and milk in a bowl with a wire whisk until thoroughly blended.
Add spices and mix again.
Place pie shell on oven rack and pour custard over to prevent spilling.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend and then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 10 in. tube or bundt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-55 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: aunt kay's bean dish
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover.
Next day, add remaining ingredients and bake, covered, at 250° for 6 to 8 hours.

title: believe it or not peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° until brown around edges.

title: beef goulash(yields 50 servings)
directions: Saute bacon and onions.
Add ground meat and brown.
Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Add meat mixture, salt, pepper, tomatoes, tomato paste and peas to macaroni.
Place in baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Season beef.
Brown in oil.
Drain excess fat.
Top with onion and ketchup.
Cover.
Braise on simmer 5 hours.
A rich, tomatoey gravy will develop.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cheese, 1 tablespoon butter and milk until smooth.
Add chicken, onion, salt and pepper.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle. Pull four corners of dough to top center over chicken mixture and twist slightly.
Then seal edges.
Brush with remaining butter. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Put in crock-pot and heat until well blended.
Serve on tortilla chips or whatever.
Good served over mashed potatoes.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into small balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: working woman's pie
directions: Pour crushed pineapple into a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Cover with cake mix.
Pour margarine on top of cake mix and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: bacon-water chestnuts appetizers
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: country fare pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs well.
Add corn syrup to eggs, beating constantly.
Combine eggs and syrup with creamed mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Add milk and salt.
Remove from heat, add nuts and vanilla.
Spread into waxed paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours until firm.
Turn onto cutting board.
Peel off paper and cut into squares. Keep refrigerated.

title: navajo sandwich
directions: Place meat slices on 1/2 of the fry bread. Add cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions and green chili. Fold over other 1/2 of fry bread and secure with toothpicks. Serve with garnishments and chips.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick vegetable coating.

title: hot perked punch
directions: Put spices in basket of percolator and perk juices in bottom.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Put mixture in the orange shells; place a marshmallow on the top and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until marshmallow browns.

title: nut loaf bread
directions: Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes in a 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan.

title: shelby's gingersnaps
directions: Cream	first	four
ingredients.
Combine
remaining ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Roll in a ball and roll in granulated	sugar.	Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Dip in almond bark or 2 pkg. chocolate chips and 1/4 lb. of paraffin.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 cup flour, working in well. Add remaining flour, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Blend well.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: batter cookie
directions: Cream sugar, oil and powdered sugar. Add soft butter, eggs, flour which has been sifted with soda, cream of tartar and salt. Mix well. Add vanilla. Chill. Make inch ball, then flatten. Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until light brown.

title: apple pie(no sugar)
directions: Put apple juice, cornstarch and apples into a pan.
Heat; let thicken.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Put 3 or 4 slices of margarine on top.
Take another pie crust and put on top.
Punch holes in top crust.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: baked filet of sole
directions: Lay fillets in baking pan and sprinkle with paprika.
Melt butter and combine with rest of ingredients.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until flakes easily.

title: meat loaf - barbecue style
directions: Lightly mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Shape into loaf.
Place in shallow pan.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with rest of ingredients.
Pour over loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste several times.

title: hulu hulu style chicken
directions: Cut tomatoes and green peppers into bite size pieces.
Place all ingredients except tomatoes and meat in pan.
Mix well.
Bring to boil; add meat and tomatoes.
Mix thoroughly and cook 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: golden glow pickle relish
directions: Cut and discard seeds of cucumbers.
Dice.
Cut and dice onions and peppers.
Combine vegetables and stir in salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse, drain and rinse again.
Combine turmeric, spices, sugar and vinegar.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Cook until transparent (about 20 minutes).
Seal in jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: soda cracker caramel bars
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil or spray Pam.
Line crackers in bottom of pan.
Boil brown sugar and butter for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers; bake for 5 minutes at 350° or until crackers float to the top of pan.
Take from oven and sprinkle with milk chocolate chips.
Spread on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: apple fruit salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Add 1 cup sugar, if needed.

title: dip
directions: Cream softened cream cheese; add salsa.
Refrigerate and serve with any kind of chips.

title: golden nuggets meatballs
directions: Combine the beef, bread crumbs, green pepper, mustard, garlic salt, salt, pepper, egg and catsup.
Mix well; shape into 16 balls, allowing 3 to 4 tablespoons per ball.
Place a cheese cube in the center of each meatball, shaping the beef mixture around the cheese.
Brown the meatballs in vegetable oil, then pour off the drippings.
Add the tomato sauce, then cover tightly and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and continue simmering for 5 to 10 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.
Serve over spaghetti, if desired.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour two round 9-inch pans (cake) 1 1/2 inches deep or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs with mixer until very light and lemon colored.
Beat in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat in butter in milk mixture (boiling).

title: ham-cheese rounds
directions: Grind ham and add enough Miracle Whip to make a ham salad. Grate Cheddar cheese.
Split English muffins in half.
Spread each half with cream cheese, ham salad and top with grated cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Enjoy.

title: caramel pie
directions: Take label off milk can.
Lay on side in a boiler pan and boil for 4 hours.
Take out of water and leave in can.
Cool overnight on counter.
Open can.
Pour in pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: mustard-glazed chicken
directions: Gas Grilling:
Combine tomato sauce, olive oil, orange juice, vinegar, oregano, salt and garlic; pour over chicken in shallow dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight; turn occasionally.
Drain; save marinade.
Preheat both sides of gas grill on high for 10 minutes.
Turn both sides to low.
Place chicken on grill; close hood and cook 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn and baste often.
Just before serving, brush with mixture of honey and mustard.
Makes 6 servings.

title: deep dish apple pudding
directions: Mix apples and sugar (white).
Place in buttered baking dish. Stir sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon with melted butter. Crumble mixture over top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are soft.
Best served when warm.

title: zucchini romano
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in margarine (covered with lid). When tender, remove lid.
Add chopped tomatoes and cook until heated through.
Place on serving dish and sprinkle with cheese.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Using low heat, stir constantly.
When melted, remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon green food coloring and the vanilla. Add more food coloring if desired.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop mixture onto wax paper, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Decorate with red cinnamon candies.
Let stand 30 minutes, until cool.

title: little pecan pies
directions: Cream oleo and cream cheese until blended.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Let stand for one hour.
Double this as filling will make 48 pies in little pans.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles, drain well.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter.
Mix well with all other ingredients.
Add crumbled cornflakes as topping.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter and light cream.
Bake 1/2 this batter for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour over caramels and 1/3 cup light cream.
Melt caramels with cream, stir thoroughly.
Add 2 tablespoons light cream to remaining batter.
Carefully spread rest of batter over caramel mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Do not overbake.
It should be moist.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put everything together except sugar, then sprinkle sugar over the top.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Mix and serve.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Drain this fruit (very well).
Save 2 1/2 cups juices from the fruit (pineapple and orange juice).

title: pralines
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring over medium heat.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in flavorings.
Beat to cool and thicken.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: banana-blueberry bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg together.
Beat in milk and mashed bananas.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into banana mixture until moist.
Gently fold in blueberries and nuts.

title: coconut bonbon candy
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar and milk with an electric mixer. Add coconut and nuts; mix with hands.
Press on a cookie sheet, covered with wax paper.
Double paper back over candy and chill overnight.

title: phony ice cream(it's an ice cream cone filled with cake.)
directions: Prepare a cake mix according to directions on the package. Spoon cake batter into flat-bottom ice cream cones until they are not quite full.

title: hot 'n' spicy eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into strips.
Slice garlic; cut hot peppers into small pieces.
Put oil into pan and heat it.
Add garlic, pepper and eggplant in order given.
Stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce, salt, sugar and water.
Stew for 4 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve when eggplant is tender.

title: apricot beer cookies
directions: Mix like pie dough the first 5 ingredients.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 bottle beer.
Roll half like pie dough to fit a large cookie sheet.
Spread filling over top.
Roll other half of dough and place over filling.
Sprinkle water over top, then sprinkle with powdered sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter meltaway cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in pan over low heat until it bubbles.
Take off heat and add next 4 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix peanut butter and oil.
Spread over cake. Put into refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Heat margarine and cocoa until it bubbles.
Add confectioners sugar, buttermilk and vanilla.
Spread over peanut butter and refrigerate.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar, vanilla and peanut butter in bowl.
Shape into balls.
Place in refrigerator.
In a pot on the stove, mix wax and chocolate bits.
Melt, do not boil. Dip balls from teaspoon into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Makes 120 balls.

title: avocado salad or dip
directions: Mash garlic with salt in bottom of bowl.
Peel ripe avocados and chop into same bowl.
Squeeze lime over avocados and mash with fork.
Add chopped tomatoes and chopped onions and mix thoroughly. Put 1 avocado seed into mixture until ready to serve.
Serve with chips as dip or use as salad served on lettuce leaf.

title: orzo and rice pilaf
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add orzo and cook until golden (stirring often) about 10 minutes.
Stir in 4 cups water, rice and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and orzo and rice are tender.
Top with parsley and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bacon-tomato grilled cheese
directions: Top 1 slice of bread with 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese, 1/4 of the tomato slices, 2 bacon strips, 1 tablespoon sour cream, 1 tablespoon onion, a pinch of oregano, 1 slice of Cheddar cheese; then top with another bread slice. Spread melted butter on the outside.

title: celery shrimp casserole
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, saut celery, green pepper and onions in margarine for 10 minutes.
Stir in all the remaining ingredients, except for cheese, and spoon the mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and put back in oven until melted.
Serves 4.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In a large mixing bowl, combine the oats, almonds and wheat germ; set aside. Stir together honey and apple juice concentrate. Pour over oat mixture, stirring until coated. Spread mixture evenly in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown. Stir every 15 minutes and several times during the last 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Stir in raisins and dried fruit. Transfer to another pan and cool. Store in airtight container. Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs, butter, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Add layer of each:
coconut, chocolate chips and nuts. Pour milk over all; do not stir.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely, then cut into bars.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites and salt. Add sugar gradually, then coconut, cornflakes and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour. Drop by spoonfuls on greased pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine milk, flour and 1/2 cup sugar in bowl; mix thoroughly.
Pour into pan over melted margarine.
Do not stir.

title: chicken onion scallop
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the onions. Make gravy with 1 1/4 cups milk.
Stir into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: cowboy sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt into large bowl; pour in starter.
Mix to make a firm dough.
Grease a 12-in. iron skillet.
Pinch off balls the size of walnuts.
Place in pan.
Set biscuits in warm place 10-15 minutes.
Bake in a 400 degree oven for 24-30 minutes.

title: heavenly fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in top of double boiler.
Combine sugar and salt; slowly add 1/2 cup at a time, alternating with 1/2 cup or so of the milk at a time; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla. Cook about 8 minutes (or until sauce begins to thicken).
Keeps well in refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: mushroom pilaf
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole dish and add rice, broth and soup.
Top mixture with mushrooms.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 55 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Uncover and top with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes more.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In baking dish, mix the green beans, soup and 1/2 can of onions.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: eggs-a-brunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage in skillet. Drain fat. Place crescent rolls at the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Press edges together. Beat together the eggs as you would for scrambled eggs. Spread sausage over rolls. Spread cheese over sausage.
Pour beaten eggs over sausage and cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Sift flour into a large bowl.
Make a hole in the middle of the flour.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Scald the milk and add 2 1/2 cups water to cool milk to lukewarm.
Put all into the flour and beat with mixer until stiff.
Finish mixing by hand and add more flour and knead.
Add more flour until your hands don't stick and work or knead for at least 5 minutes.
Cover with oil and wax paper.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Let rise again, then work out rolls.
This can also be made into about 4 loaves.
Let rise and bake at 400° for about 20 or 25 minutes. Happy baking!

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jell-O, oil and eggs and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add strawberries and beat 1 minute more, until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake 10 minutes, then turn upside down on rack.

title: nutty crackers
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Spread on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: quick party log
directions: Melt chocolate morsels over hot water. Transfer to small bowl and blend in sour cream, vanilla and salt. Gradually add confectioners sugar and beat until smooth.
Place pound cakes, end to end, to form one long cake. Cut cake crosswise into three layers. Fill and frost cake with prepared frosting.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings in mixing bowl, beating lightly.
Sir in sausage.
(For one quiche, you will have 2 eggs, 1/2 cup milk, salt, pepper and 1/2 browned sausage.)
Sprinkle 1/2 of the grated hunk cheese over pastry shell.
Then pour in sausage mixture.
Sprinkle top with remaining grated cheese.

title: shrimp in sour cream
directions: Saute shrimp and garlic in melted butter.
Add drained mushrooms, green onions and parsley.
Stir in flour to thicken. Add Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Add sour cream.
Serve over hot rice.

title: egg, muffin and o.j.
directions: You will need a Ziploc bag and a straw.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread; cool, crumble and set aside.
Combine tomatoes, peppers, onion, pickles and bacon.
Toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice; stir well.
Set aside.

title: norwegian-american lefse
directions: Night Before:
Peel, salt and boil potatoes until done.
Drain and mash well.
Add butter, Crisco, sugar, salt and lard; whip up until smooth.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets to cool.
Put in large bowl and store, uncovered, overnight at room temperature.
Mix 4 cups cooled mashed potato mixture with 1 1/4 cups flour or less in a bowl.
Spread flour on your tabletop; knead the potatoes until the flour has been used to make a soft dough.
Roll dough into a large roll; cut in half.
Place 1/2 in a covered Tupperware bowl. Cut the other half into small pieces, about 1/2 cup size.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: Put minced garlic, 1/3 of the sour cream, vegetable oil, vinegar, herbs and mayonnaise in blender and mix at high speed. (Use electric mixer if you have no blender.)
Empty blender contents into bowl and add remaining sour cream.
Blend with wooden spoon until just mixed.
Chill if desired.

title: apple pie
directions: Add half of the apples.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Add remaining apples.
Moisten edge of pastry with water.
Press two crusts together.
Prick top with fork.
Brush with cream.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
The top browns quickly; cover loosely with foil.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat them well in oven.
Add French fried onion rings to top and bake until bubbling.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Heat together over low heat the chocolate chips, margarine and milk.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cookies will be soft.
Do not overcook.
Carefully remove cookies from sheet and let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate-p-nut butter fudge
directions: Melt chocolate drops in microwave exactly 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter until well mixed.
Pour onto buttered shallow pan or cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Cut in pieces.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts, in large mixing bowl.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Spoon hot butter around and over cake.

title: home ec special chocolate crinkles
directions: If using squares of chocolate, in a small saucepan, melt chocolate squares over low heat, stirring often.
Remove from heat and let cool.
In a large mixing bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, cooking oil, vanilla and melted and cooled chocolate or premelted chocolate product with a wooden spoon.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour and baking powder.
Gradually add to chocolate mixture, stirring with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients for 1 to 2 minutes on medium speed of mixer.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir together, then spoon in greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leave in pan to cool.

title: gin-marinated olives
directions: Place ingredients in a glass bowl. Cover with cheesecloth. Set aside in cool place for 2 days.
Drain off gin (save) and discard juniper berries and peppercorns.
Makes 1 cup (about 28 medium) marinated olives.

title: caramel rice krispie treats
directions: Melt caramels with water.
Pour over Rice Krispies and peanuts or coconut.
Stir.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chips. Bake at 200° for 10 minutes or until chips are melted. Smooth chips with spoon or spatula. Cool and cut into small pieces.

title: ham and fruit sandwiches(appetizers)
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the ham, apple, pineapple, celery and sandwich spread.
Spread each toast slice with about 1/3 cup of the ham mixture.
Top each with cheese and apple slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tropical gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all the other ingredients in order.
Bake in a greased shallow pan in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, then add dressing mix. Mix well.
Roll into ball or log, then into the chili powder and pecans.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and let them melt.
Add the flour to sugar, cold water, eggs and yeast mixture.
Let rise in refrigerator, covered, overnight.
Shape into rolls and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350°.

title: prize winning recipe(if you want a good pie!)
directions: Blend cream cheese until creamy.
Add the Eagle Brand milk; blend well.
Add water; blend.
Add instant pudding; blend.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust and chill.

title: apple pear salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, milk and salt; beat with a fork until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tangy tomato-raspberry salad
directions: Add enough water to tomatoes to make 2 cups.
Place in a saucepan, breaking up tomatoes with the edge of spoon.
Bring to a boil.
Add gelatin and Worcestershire sauce, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Pour into an oiled 2-cup mold or bowl and refrigerate until firm.

title: good vegetable salad
directions: Saute onions and celery until tender.
Thaw broccoli and cauliflower, cut into bite size pieces.
Put all ingredients in broiler pan that is oiled after you saute.
Bring to a boil until all cheese is melted.
Butter a baking dish and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 50 minutes.
Do not overcook.
These tablespoons of coconut can be added for a variation.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl, cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add bananas and eggs.
Blend together.
Sift flour, salt and soda. Carefully blend banana mixture and flour mixture.
Do not overmix. Pour batter in 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Enjoy!

title: mount rainier cookies
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy and lemon colored.
Add slowly the powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows. Add cooled chocolate and butter.
Have fine grated coconut in a bowl.
Drop cookies into coconut and roll until covered.
Set aside to firm and set.
These are very rich.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks and blend milk. Add vanilla and butter.
Cook until thick over medium heat.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Make top with egg whites.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans well. Beat eggs and add all together. Put in pie shells and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 300°. Makes 3 pies.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch sheet cake pan.
Layer pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour cake mix over top of coconut.
Mix softened margarine, softened cream cheese and one box confectioners sugar until well blended by mixer. Drop by spoonfuls until entire cake is covered.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let sit for 5 to 15 minutes.
Turn out on foil paper or square cake dish.
Yummy!

title: 10 cup cookies
directions: Drop by spoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: "non-edible" dough art
directions: Combine ingredients in pan.
Cook on low heat, stirring continuously, for about 5 minutes, or until mixture thickens and forms into a ball.
Knead by hand until smooth.
Form into jewelry, figurines, small sculpture or objets d'art.
Dry in a dehydrator or very low oven; paint when dried, if desired.
Finish by spraying with a clear polyurethane to seal and protect.

title: strawberry banana flip out
directions: Puree strawberries.
Add eggs whites, banana, yogurt and honey and blend until smooth.

title: sausage gravy
directions: If not enough grease in pan after cooking sausage add bacon grease.
Add flour to pan and stir together.
Add water stirring constantly until thickened.
Add milk gradually until right consistency.
Serve over biscuits.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add additional juice to make 2 cups.
Put in saucepan; add pudding mix in juice.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Return fruit to mixture.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients on medium-high heat.
Stir and cook to 250°.
Put in food coloring to desired color and continue cooking to 280°.
Take off heat and let temperature rise to 300°. Put in the cinnamon oil.
I put on a cookie sheet covered with powdered sugar.
Score with spatula (or I use a pizza cutter) before it gets too hard to cut.
Allow to cool, then put in airtight container.

title: fettuccine with fresh tomatoes and basil
directions: Cook fettuccine.
In heavy skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add tomatoes, garlic, basil and sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add parsley and pepper.
Add to tomato mixture with cheese; toss to mix.
Makes 2 main courses or 4 appetizers.

title: meat marinade
directions: This is a favorite marinade for grilled chicken.
May also be used to marinate beef sirloin cubes for shish kabob.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with topping.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 15 servings.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Bake eggplant in oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Scoop out pulp into blender.
Slowly pour in oil while blending.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: green chile quiche
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into Pet-Ritz deep dish pie shell. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
