Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, bananas, vanilla and sour cream. Stir in flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the cinnamon mixture in greased and floured Bundt pan. Spoon in half of the batter.
Repeat layers, ending with cinnamon mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May use small loaf pans; bake 30 minutes.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer all items in order listed in a 9 x 12 inch dish.

title: bleu cheese cheeseball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into ball. Roll in chopped pecans or parsley. Refrigerate.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: tomato-topped fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium-low heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp, turning often. Remove bacon and drain on paper towels.
Add onion to drippings in skillet.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until tender; drain.
Stir in tomato.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through.
Crumble bacon and stir into tomato mixture.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook milk, flour/sugar mixture, cocoa and egg yolks on high until thick.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add tomatoes, garlic powder, tomato sauce, tomato paste, oregano, basil, salt and pepper and simmer.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package.
Place 1 layer of noodles in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Use layers of meat mixture, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a rapid boil with salt.
Gradually stir in grits with a fork.
Cook until all water is absorbed.
Stir in butter, a little at a time.
Carefully add eggs, cheese, garlic and cayenne pepper.
Put into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well the sugar, shortening and egg. Stir in milk and bananas.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir banana mixture into batter.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Done when toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 350°. Coconut and dates are also good added to this recipe.

title: cabbage-rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, celery, onion, and salt.
In a skillet, cook cabbage for 5 minutes.
After it starts boiling, drain and add meat mixture.
Add rice and 1/4 c. cheese.
Put in casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: orange pumpkin bread
directions: Soak the golden raisins and black raisins in Amaretto or whiskey.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix butter and cracker crumbs and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over chilled crumbs.
Sprinkle nuts over cream cheese.
Spread Cool Whip over nuts.
Spread fruit over Cool Whip and chill.
(I use fresh fruit but you can use any can of pie filling.)

title: hard candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat
until
sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature
reaches
310°	or until drops of syrup form hard, brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto lightly greased
cookie
sheet
and cool.
Break into pieces. Coat with powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Makes in excess of 2 pounds.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour mixed with baking powder and beat.
Slowly add nuts and flavorings.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pizzaburger loaf
directions: Sauce:
Combine onions, tomato paste and water in saucepan and simmer 20 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Add cheese, onion, pepper and pimento.
Stir in macaroni.
Put in casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 350° until brown and bubbly (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: beef oriental
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer and ginger; let stand for 30 minutes.
In a large skillet; stir-fry vegetables in 2 tablespoons of hot oil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil to skillet.
Cook meat, onion and garlic; stir-fry 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add liquid and vegetables to meat in skillet. Cook, stirring continuously until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add tomato sauce and water.
Boil until thickened.
Add
kidney beans, salt and pepper.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown pork chops in skillet with small amount of fat.
Pour rice into baking dish and place browned pork chops over rice.
Peel and cut onion into 4 slices and place on chops. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cut lemon into 4 slices and set on top of onion.
Pour bouillon over all. Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Pour chilled ginger ale into large punch bowl. Add chilled fruit juices. Stir gently. With scoop, dip sherbet into bowl until entire surface is covered. With punch dipper, dip punch over sherbet until pieces of sherbet are fairly small. Use flavor of sherbet to match desired color.

title: diet cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: almond heath candy
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add sugar and syrup.
Cook to hard ball stage.
This will turn brown color and smoke.
Add almonds. Put in buttered cookie sheet pan and let cool.

title: not to eat! (but still a treat)
directions: Cook all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes, stirring vigorously, until mixture forms a ball. Remove dough from saucepan and let stand on counter 5 minutes. Knead dough about 30 seconds or until smooth and blended.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Entertain your child with creative dough while you cook!

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taos bread pudding
directions: Add brown sugar to boiling water; add butter until melted (set aside).
Cut up bread into cubes.
Layer bread with sliced cheese and raisins.
Repeat layers.
Pour the brown sugar mixture over the bread.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts, about 25 minutes.

title: elegant steak
directions: Wash meat, tenderize and poke with a fork.
Turn and repeat. Put in a pan lined with heavy foil.
Sprinkle tomato sauce, 1 package dried onion soup mix, garlic, 1/2 to 1 teaspoon oregano and 2 teaspoons dried parsley.
Seal foil and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 300° to 350°.
Slice at diagonal, thinly.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread coconut and then the nuts on the bottom of the pan.

title: tuna rolls
directions: Drain fish and mix with mayonnaise.
Make 2 long strips with crescent rolls; pinch perforated parts together.
Spread fish mixture on strips and roll jelly roll fashion.
Cut each roll into 5 slices.
Heat as instructed.
Heat soup as instructed.
Serve hot and cover with soup.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, baking soda and salt in medium size bowl.
Cut in chilled butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead lightly, about 10 strokes.
Roll dough 1 1/2-inches thick.
Cut into 3-inch circles.

title: silly putty
directions: Mix starch with glue until it turns into a solid mass.
Silly putty should break apart when pulled.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and peanut butter in a saucepan.
Blend together until smooth and boiling.
Remove from heat and immediately pour onto corn flakes.
Corn flakes should be in a large round bowl.
Stir the mixture together until all corn flakes are covered.
Spoon out of bowl onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: deep dish mexican pie
directions: Thaw pie crust and bake 10 minutes.
Mix beans and picante sauce.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Brown meat and add seasoning as directed on package.
Spread half of mixture on top of beans.
Add a layer of 1 cup cheese and a layer of Tostitos.
Repeat layers, except chips.

title: spinach lasagna rolls
directions: Drain spinach; squeeze out liquid.
Microwave spinach until done; drain again.
Cook beef and onions until brown.
Drain fat. Stir together cottage cheese, egg, seasonings, garlic and salt. Mix with meat and onions.
Spread mixture on noodles; roll them up.
Place seam side down in oblong baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over rolls.
Bake in oven for about 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with grated cheese before serving.
Makes an excellent low-fat meal with a tossed salad.

title: alfredo with zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into long strips that resemble fettuccine noodles (8 cups total are needed).
Toss zucchini with salt. Drain for 1 hour.
Rinse; drain and pat dry.
Over medium-high heat, cook zucchini in oil and garlic (approximately 2 to 4 minutes).
Transfer to a large bowl.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until foamy.
Add walnuts and mix until coated.
In a paper bag, put sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Shake to mix.
Add coated walnuts and shake until all walnuts are covered with sugar mixture.
Put on greased cookie sheet and bake for 1/2 hour at 250°.
Then reduce heat to 200° and bake for 1/2 hour more. Stir walnuts after first 1/2 hour of baking.
Allow to cool and store in airtight container.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions and salt together and let stand all day or overnight.
Drain well and add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: yams and peaches
directions: Arrange yams and peaches in a dish.
Pour brown sugar mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is a very pretty dish.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: *Batter should be thin enough to spread out when dropped in hot shortening.
You can tell by the first one you cook.

title: peach dessert
directions: Spray 8 x 13-inch pan.
Add peaches.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Add nuts and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes; cool.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: butterscotch treats
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and peanut butter in a double boiler. Stir in potato sticks and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: buttermilk bannock
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or fingers. Add buttermilk, all at once, stirring with a fork to make a soft, sticky dough.
Add a little more buttermilk if dough is too dry. With floured hands, pat dough evenly into greased 9-inch round cake pan.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken breasts.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and onion.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 6 minutes.
Add soup, mushrooms with liquid and water.
Heat to boiling and continue stirring until mixture is smooth.
Reduce heat and stir in sour cream.
Do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli heads and tender part of stems.
Stir sugar, Parmesan cheese and chopped onion into mayonnaise.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place broccoli in the casserole dish.
Lay chicken meat over the broccoli.
Mix the next 6 ingredients (and any optional ingredients) and pour over the chicken and broccoli.
Top with crushed crackers and more grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer ingredients in order listed in ungreased oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Press first 2 ingredients into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until edges brown.
With electric mixer, blend next 3 ingredients.
Pour over cooled crumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces; fry lightly in saucepan.
Remove from pan.
Saute onions in bacon fat.
Add water and potatoes. Cook until potatoes are done.
Add canned milk, corn, bacon and seasonings.
Heat and serve.
If fresh corn is used, cook with potatoes.

title: dad's fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour two 4 x 8-inch loaf pans; preheat oven to 300°.
Break eggs into bowl and beat thoroughly; add sugar and beat well.
Add baking powder and salt to flour and mix.
Stir flour mixture into the eggs and sugar batter; add nuts and fruit.
The pecans, cherries and dates are to be added whole.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: bess truman's ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar until smooth.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into egg mixture. Add apple, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in buttered pie pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream. Serves 6.

title: tuna casserole(low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
This takes about 20 minutes.
One serving equals 175 calories.
Serves

title: parmesan chicken bake
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and garlic salt.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then coat with crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally with remaining melted butter.

title: orange candied yams
directions: Boil yams until tender.
Drain, cool, peel, and cut in half. Put sugar, butter, orange juice and grated rind in a large skillet.
Heat slowly, stirring occasionally.
Simmer the yams, a few at a time in the mixture over low heat until all are glazed. Remove to a baking dish.
Heat the orange sections for 2-3 minutes in the skillet, arrange over yams in serving dish.

title: orange filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly until well thickened, about 10 minutes.
Chill well before spreading on cake.

title: baked rice with sausage
directions: In skillet, cook sausage, onion, and pepper until meat isn't pink and vegetables are tender. Stir in soup, rice, and sausage mixture. Mix well. Put in well greased 13 X 9 baking dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. toss bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over mixture and bake uncovered for another 10-15 minutes, or until rice is tender. Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: flounder fillets baked in sour cream
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish with 1 teaspoon of the butter. Arrange fish in a baking dish.
Blend salt, Tabasco sauce, paprika and Parmesan cheese into sour cream.
Spread over fish.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with remaining 3 teaspoons butter.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes until fish is easily flaked with a fork.
Serve with lemon slices.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cornstarch, then add vinegar and water and cook until hot.
Add beets and let stand at least 30 minutes.
Just before serving, bring to boiling point and add 2 tablespoons of butter.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Bake cake; cook pudding.
Punch holes in cake with fork and pour pudding over cake.
Boil pineapple with 1 cup sugar; pour over cake.
Layer Cool Whip over cake then add coconut.

title: corn bread deluxe
directions: Preheat oven .
Mix ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Coat each piece of chicken with flour mixture. Reserve 2 tablespoons remaining flour mixture. Brown chicken in shortening. Place chicken in 2-quart baking dish and sprinkle with onion, carrots and mushrooms. Blend reserved flour mixture, brown sugar, ginger and salt into drippings. Stir to make a smooth paste. Add orange juice concentrate and water. Cook until bubbly. Pour over chicken and vegetables. Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve over rice.

title: dam biscuits
directions: In a large bowl combine first 4 ingredients with a pastry blender. Cut in shortening until coarse crumbles. Place warm water in a bowl; add yeast. Stir until dissolved. Add yeast mixture and buttermilk to dry mixture and blend well. Roll dough on floured surface to 3/4 inch thick. Cut into 2 1/2 inch biscuits, cover and let rise until double, about 45 minutes. Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: angel food pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt together, then stir into rapidly boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Cool and add vanilla (optional:
add 1/2 teaspoon almond extract).
Stir in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into cooked pie shells.
Cover with whipped cream and coconut.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: indian fried eggplant
directions: Wash eggplant.
Beat remaining ingredients with beater until smooth.
Heat oil to 375° in a skillet.
Slice eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip slices into batter.
Let excess drip off. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: frozen punch
directions: Make syrup of sugar and boiling water.
Add gelatin to hot syrup.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool syrup.
Mix in lemonade, orange juice, pineapple juice, water and almond extract.
Freeze. Thaw at room temperature for about 3 hours, before serving.
When ready to serve add ginger ale.
Serves 100.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine
all
ingredients;
mix
well.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into
hot oil in skillet.
Flatten patties out and cook until golden brown.
Turn and brown on both sides.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour and water over medium heat.
Add 3 ounces of Jell-O.
Let cool, then add strawberries.
Cook pie shells as directed on package.
Add mixture to each pie shell.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line large baking dish with layer of tortillas.
Sprinkle with chicken broth.
Saute onions and green peppers.
Add soups and chili powder.
Pour layer of soup mixture over tortillas, then a layer of chicken, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour over all the Ro-Tel or the tomato soup with chili powder.
For a milder taste, use 1/2 can Ro-Tel and 1/2 can plain tomatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with vegetable salad and Mexican rice or beans.

title: pineapple cheese frosting
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, cheese cake filling mix and sour cream.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: 90 minute rolls
directions: Heat milk, water and butter (do not boil).
Combine all dry ingredients in medium mixing bowl.
Add hot liquids; beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Turn onto a floured board.
Knead 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; grease top.
Cover and place bowl into large pan of very warm water.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Shape into smooth balls and place in greased baking pan.
Cover and place pan over very warm water.
Let rise 15 to 25 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: quick bread
directions: Combine
water,
yeast
and
honey.
Stir
until
yeast dissolves.
Add
cups flour and salt.
Beat hard with a big spoon until
batter
is smooth.
Add remaining flour and blend well.
Pour oil
over dough while in the bowl and knead just 2 or 3
minutes.
The
oil will be absorbed by the dough.
Cover and let
rise until doubled.
Punch down and turn onto lightly floured board and knead slightly.
Shape into 2 loaves and put into greased
bread
pans.
Cover
and let rise until doubled. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: twice-baked mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cook in water until tender. Drain. Mash potatoes with potato masher. Add desired amount of butter, cheese, sour cream and bacon bits. Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture into casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk to a boil and boil for 1 minute only.
Remove from heat and add salt, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper to cool.
Shape with fork.

title: empress beef
directions: Heat oil in skillet, add beef and salt.
Stir and brown for about 5 minutes.
Add onion, celery, beans, mushrooms, carrots and water chestnuts.
Stir and cook on high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: olvita crostini
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Arrange bread slices on baking sheet. Spread olive mixture over each.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes until toasted and bubbly.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute first four ingredients until almost done.
Cook next 3 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Add mushrooms, including liquid (if too dry, add 1/2 cup water).
Bake (covered) at 350° for 1/2 hour (in a glass casserole, bake at 325°).

title: almond pecan corn
directions: Toast pecans and almonds on baking sheet in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Combine popcorn and nuts in lightly oiled bowl.
Toss to distribute evenly.
Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan and bring mixture to boil over high heat, washing down any sugar and crystals clinging to sides of pan with pastry brush dipped into cold water.
Add butter and continue cooking until candy thermometer registers 300°.
Pour hot syrup over popcorn and nut mixture.
Quickly toss to coat mixture with caramel and spread it in a thin layer of two lightly oiled baking sheets.
Cool completely before breaking into bite-size pieces. Store in airtight containers until ready to use.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Tear off bone in pieces.
In a pan, place a thin layer of the dressing mix.
Melt the margarine in the broth where you cooked the chicken.
Mix 1 can of broth with 2 cans soup.
Place a layer of chicken on top of crumbs.
Pour half of the soup mix on top of crumbs.
Repeat the layers ending with sprinkling of bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: one yolk egg salad
directions: Boil the eggs.
Run them under cold water and peel.
Separate the whites from the yolks.
Discard all but one yolk.
Chop the eggs and combine them with ingredients.
Serves 2 people.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, cook onions and peppers in butter or oil until tender.
Stir in salt, pepper, oregano and fresh garlic.
In large bowl, combine eggs, ham, cheese, onions and peppers.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all together in greased dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: just really good punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with 4 cups water.
Make a light syrup of sugar, 4 cups water, apple juice and pineapple juice.
Mix lemonade with water it calls for (about one gallon).
Just before serving, add extract and ginger ale.
This can be frozen and served as slush. Serves 45.

title: broccoli puree with parmesan and nutmeg
directions: Cut broccoli stems into 1-inch pieces.
Cut tops into florets. Bring large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add broccoli stems and cook 6 minutes.
Add broccoli florets and cook until stems and florets are very tender, about 6 more minutes.
Drain well. Reserve 10 florets.
Put rest of broccoli in processor.
Add butter and puree about 5 minutes.
Blend in cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
To serve, reheat and garnish with reserved florets.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and egg together.
Add enough water to make dough.
Roll out on floured surface.
Slice into squares.
Drop in boiling broth and let boil for 20 minutes.

title: lauren's special recipe
directions: Dust chicken with 2 teaspoons butter and flour.
Cook in oil and garlic for 3 minutes on each side.
Melt butter in another pan.
Add mushrooms, shrimp, tomatoes and asparagus.
Add wine and chicken.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Heat
oven
Grate cheese and place on tortillas. Top
with tomato.
Heat 10 minutes or until crisp (light brown edges).
Goes well with taco sauce on top.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Cook
and
stir
beef,
garlic
and
onion until brown. Drain. Add pepper, chili sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 10
minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on warmed buns with potato
chips, carrot
and celery sticks.
Makes enough for 6 buns.

title: split pea soup
directions: Place the water in a large soup pot. Add peas, limas, barley, onion, bay leaf and celery.
Seed and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook an additional 45 minutes to 60 minutes.
Serves 4.
Cooking time is 2 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry-sour cream bread
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix baking mix, sugar, sour cream, oil, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs; beat 50 strokes.
Stir in nuts and strawberries.
Pour into pan. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Spread Sour Cream Glaze over top of loaf; garnish as desired.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat, then add pumpkin, then rolled oats and dry ingredients, vanilla, bits and nuts.
Grease cookie sheets.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 14 minutes.

title: cheesecake creme dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme, mixing until well blended.
Serve with sliced apples, fresh pineapple, orange sections, pears, bananas, strawberries or kiwi.
Yields 2 cups.

title: banana nut bread
directions: *Omit if using self-rising flour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not overbake.

title: molasses cookies(aunt johanna 1930)
directions: Cover with Saran Wrap in refrigerator to cool.
Roll out batter; sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Cut up vegetables as for any stew.
Put in oven for 4 hours at 300°.
Cover tightly with foil.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 12 muffins (use all batter and divide in cups; I use paper liners).
Bake 18 minutes.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine ingredients, except vanilla.
Cook in double boiler. Beat while cooking (7 minutes), then add vanilla.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening, milk and yeast.
Knead enough to hold together.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mamaw's pineapple icing
directions: Mix pineapple filling, cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; ice the angel food cake. You can also use crushed pineapple and 3 tablespoons corn starch; cook until thick. Let cool, then mix with other ingredients.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Combine mustard and jelly in a crock-pot on low.
When melted, place sausage in and heat through.

title: instant squash
directions: Melt just enough margarine to cover bottom of frypan.
Shred squash on coarse side of grater.
Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add squash and saute over medium heat, stirring constantly (1 to 3 minutes).
Squash will be crispy.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve as vegetable side dish.

title: chinese noodle soup
directions: Mix all dressing ingredients together.
Deep fat fry wonton skins and rice sticks.
Mix salad ingredients except fried wontons, rice sticks and dressing.
Add these just before serving.

title: pickled banana peppers
directions: Bring to boil the vinegar and sugar. Place salt, turmeric and mustard seed in a pint jar. Add sliced pepper rings. Pour vinegar mixture over pepper rings and seal jars. Turn upside down for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Put 1/2 tablespoon butter in a 9-inch frypan or crepe pan.
Add 2 tablespoons of mixture and spread quickly around the pan.
Cook until dry on the top and remove.
Spread with butter, sugar and cinnamon and roll up.
Also good with honey or syrup or whatever you like.
Half recipe for smaller batch!

title: linguini and spinach
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Cook spinach and garlic 5 minutes, stirring. Dissolve bouillon in water. Add to spinach along with basil and Feta. Stir until blended. Toss with linguini and grated cheese.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and let cool.
Cut into bite sizes.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add peas and carrots after drained.
Dice 4 potatoes over top.
Add onion flakes, salt and pepper to taste, garlic salt and tarragon flakes.
Mix cream of chicken soup, 1 can water and broth from chicken.
Place pie crust on top.
Put 1 stick margarine on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fat-free marshmallow treats
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with no-stick spray.
Melt marshmallows over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat. Add Molly McButter; mix well.
Quickly add cereal and raisins. Stir until well coated.
Press evenly into prepared pan.
Cool; cut into bars.
Yields 16 bars.
Calories: 100.
Fat: 0.

title: catalina berry chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in 1/4 cup of the dressing in medium skillet on medium heat 8 minutes or until cooked through. Toss greens, strawberries, almonds and chicken in large salad bowl. Drizzle with remaining 3/4 cup dressing. Toss. Makes 4 servings.

title: almost heavenly cake
directions: Bake the cake mix according to instructions on box in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
While the cake is still hot, poke full of holes with a fork.
Spread the crushed pineapple, juice and all, on top of cake.
Whip the milk, pudding and cream cheese with mixer.
Spread this in cooled cake; sprinkle nuts on topping.

title: grandmother's famous relish
directions: Cut tomatoes in large cubes.
Dice pepper and onion in bowl. Mix vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper together.
Pour over vegetables.
Serves about 6.

title: easy mexican cheese bread
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Place side by side on ungreased baking sheet with long edges overlapping slightly to form 13 x 7-inch rectangle.
Press perforations and edges to seal. Spread beans in 2-inch wide strip down center of dough length. Top with 1/2 cup cheese and 1/4 cup salsa.
Make cuts from filling to dough edge 1 1/2 inches apart on each side of rectangle.
Fold strips of dough at angles over filling, alternating from side to side.
Seal.

title: deluxe cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, mix flour and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Roll or pat dough onto bottom and sides of 9-inch springform pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
In a large bowl, beat cheese until soft.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; blend into cheese.
Add rinds.
Add eggs and yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in cream.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 225°; bake 1 hour longer or until toothpick comes out clean.
Turn oven off. Leave in oven about 15 minutes.
Remove to cake rack.
Cool away from drafts.
When cool, remove side of pan.
Place on serving plate.
Decorate with whipped cream or strawberry glaze or pineapple glaze.

title: poppy seed cake (or muffins)
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Batter will be somewhat thick.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan or mini or standard cupcake papers in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until top springs back from touch.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and molasses.
Mix in salt and egg. Dissolve soda in water.
Sift dry ingredients and add with water. Set aside for 20 minutes.
Shape dough into small balls.
Flatten balls and press with fork dipped in water.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut or pecan brittle(makes approximately 5 pounds)
directions: Butter 4 large cookie sheets.
Butter your 5 or 6-quart saucepan.
Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Heat on medium or a little above medium.
With candy thermometer in pan, cook until it reaches 275°, stirring constantly.
Stir in nuts.
Continue cooking until it reaches 295°.
No more!
Remove from heat and instantly stir in baking soda until mixture foams up.
Quickly pour on buttered cookie sheets as thin as possible without spreading with spoon.
Pour out only.

title: bruschetta
directions: Slice fresh Italian bread.
Brush on olive oil and garlic. Toast lightly under broiler.
Pull from oven.
Sprinkle diced tomatoes, capers and fresh herbs on top of each piece of toasted bread.
Grate fresh Parmesan cheese and place bread back under broiler until cheese melts.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini ratatouille
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 10-inch baking dish or large casserole with cover.
In covered skillet, heat oil over low heat and sweat onions until soft.
Stir in garlic and re-cover for 1 minute or until garlic starts to soften.
Add peppers, celery and zucchini.
Continue to cook over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: frosted banana bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bars test done. Cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 3 hours if frozen.
Combine all ingredients, fold and mix.

title: plain meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make small balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, turning one time with spoon halfway through baking time.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in sauce.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix and roll into round rolls.
Chill.
Slice.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mandel bread(almond cake)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder and make a well.
Add remaining ingredients to well (add nuts and raisins last) and mix well.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot stuffing
directions: Prepare bread crumbs and place in large mixing bowl.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Pour over bread cubes.
Add seasonings and toss.
Moisten bread cubes with broth and place lightly into slow cooker.
(Spray a little Pam in the cooker.) Cover and set on high for 1 hour.
Turn setting to low and cook for an additional 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cucumber crisp pickle
directions: Wash cucumbers well and place whole cucumbers in crock, combine salt and water, pour over cucumbers, let soak for 14 days. Remove from salt water, rinse well in water.
Slice thin, put back in clean crock and cover with alum dissolved in 1 gal. of water.
Let stand overnight, remove from alum water, do not rinse. Place sliced cucumbers back in crock, cover with 1 gal. vinegar and let soak for 6 hours.
Remove from vinegar and pour vinegar down the drain.
Place a layer of cucumbers, a layer of sugar in a big glass jar or a crock until all are layered.
Place bag of spice in middle of layers.
Let stand in jar for 4 to 5 days. Throw spice out.
Place rest in jars.
Yield: 10 to 12 quarts.

title: crispy sesame shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine first 6 ingredients in a pie plate or shallow dish and stir well. Dip shrimp in egg white and dredge in stuffing mixture. Place shrimp on a large baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Lightly coat shrimp with cooking spray. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden. Divide shrimp evenly between 2 plates. Makes 2 servings.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Mix jello and boiling water.
Add strawberry drink.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour jello and strawberry drink mixture over cake.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Combine pudding with Cool Whip.
Spread over cake. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli slightly in salted water.
Drain well and add cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot with chips.

title: never fail "fruits cake"
directions: Moisten with 1 cup tear drops and you will have a beautiful never fail "fruits cake" that will serve many people!

title: linguine salad
directions: Boil linguine until tender.
Rinse in cool water.
Put vegetables in a bowl.
Add oil.
Mix.
Stir in linguine. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken and homemade egg noodles
directions: Boil chicken pieces with onion and poultry seasoning in 1 to 2 quarts of water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove from water to cool.
While chicken is cooking, combine egg, salt and cream.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Roll very thin on floured surface, let stand 20 minutes. Roll up and slice 1/8-inch thick.
(You can also use a pasta maker if you have one.)
Spread out and dry 1 to 2 hours.
Drop into boiling chicken stock and cook 10 minutes.
Debone chicken, flake chicken and add to noodles.
Thicken stock slightly with flour and water and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ambrosia 1
directions: Mix together and chill.
Add apple or orange juice if needed.

title: parmesan-garlic popcorn spice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Store in large spice shaker.
To serve, melt 1/4 cup butter in a small saucepan over low heat.
Stir in 1 tablespoon popcorn spice.
Pour over popped corn; stir well.

title: easy turkey breast
directions: Pour water in crock-pot.
Coat turkey breast with lemon pepper and place in crock-pot.
Turn on high and leave all day or overnight.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 4 to 5 cups boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale and sherbet, which will be added when ready to serve.

title: banana cream pudding
directions: Blend
together
pudding
mix
and
milk; then put sour cream in.
Blend
well, add Cool Whip; mix all well.
Put some of mixture in bottom of dish; then layer cookies, bananas and cream mixture.
Repeat
the layers until all of cream mixture is used up.
Top with more Cool Whip.

title: lo-fat quesadillas
directions: Put tortillas in a skillet.
Heat.
Add cheese and onions. Melt.
Put tortilla on top and flip over.
Cut into 4's.
Serve with Pace picante sauce.
Good.

title: heavenly seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions in 2 quart bowl, then spread Miracle Whip over onions, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 8 servings. Before serving, fry and crumble bacon over salad.

title: coconut balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper.
Refrigerate for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Roll balls in food coloring and sugar.

title: chocolate-covered strawberries
directions: You will also need 1 foil-lined baking sheet (place in freezer).

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and mix well.
Stir in marshmallows, bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: italian mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil, then mash potatoes.
Add butter and whip.
Add salt, pepper and parsley to the beaten eggs.
Add egg to potatoes and whip.
Fold in Prosciutto, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Butter a 3-quart casserole with 1 tablespoon butter and then sprinkle with plain bread crumbs.
Turn the potato mixture into the casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and a light sprinkle of paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until golden on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add whole eggs one at a time.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Cook 1 pound of hot sausage; drain.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam; line pan with English muffins (halve muffins, then butter). Sprinkle sausage over muffins.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over muffins and sausage.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Cover with foil for overnight; refrigerate.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, then 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients; drain off fat.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Add meat mixture; mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ripe yellow cucumber pickles
directions: Select melons with thick rinds.
Peel off all green portion. Dice.
Soak in mild salt water overnight (1/2 cup salt to 1 gallon water).
Drain.
Cook in clear water about 30 minutes until tender.
Drain.
For 4 pounds rind, make a syrup of 9 cups sugar, 8 cups water, 4 lemons, 4 sticks cinnamon and 4 teaspoon cloves (spices in cheesecloth).
Boil syrup, lemon and spices
5 minutes before adding rind.
Cook until rinds are transparent.
Can add food coloring (red, green, yellow, etc.)
Remove spice bag.
Seal.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Use skinless chicken breasts.
Bake until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat soup with 1/4 can of water.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir until heated and blended well.
Pour over cooked chicken.
Return to oven, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: seafood strudel
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter over low heat.
Stir in flour slowly to make smooth paste and heat gently.
Remove from heat. Add Dijon mustard and salt; slowly add milk.
Place over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick.
Set aside to cool.
(Will be firm.)

title: chocolate pudding mix
directions: Stir together the dry milk, sugar, cornstarch and cocoa until well mixed.
Store in a tightly covered container at room temperature.

title: round oatmeal bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add oats mixture, eggs and 3 cups flour, mix well.
Stir in enough of remaining flour to form soft dough.
Knead 5 minutes, divide into 2 loaves in 2 well-greased 10-inch pie plates.
Cover, let rise about 1 hour.
Sprinkle oats on top after gently brushing with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot spiced punch(serves 30)
directions: Place spices and sugar in basket of percolator.
Pour juices into pot.
Percolate 5 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 c juice; set pineapple aside. In small bowl or cup, combine reserved juice, the soy sauce, vinegar, and cornstarch, stirring until cornstarch is dissolved; set aside.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, remaining stick of butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Spread mixture on top of crumbs.
Slice bananas and arrange on top of mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over banana slices.
Spread whipped cream over that and top with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: polynesian pork roast
directions: Season pork roast with garlic salt.
Mix soy sauce, honey and ketchup.
Pour over pork roast.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes per pound, basting periodically with sauce.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil (or applesauce), eggs, pudding and juice. Add sugar, cinnamon and seed.
Place in greased tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and blend.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and stir until well blended.
If too soft to handle, chill dough until firm.
Roll into balls the size of large walnuts.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until set, but not hard.
Cool and store in covered box.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: When potatoes are mashed, add cream cheese in small pieces and butter. Beat until completely mixed in.
Add sour cream, eggs, milk, onion, salt and pepper. Beat until fluffy.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch casserole (round) and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Prepare a day ahead for best flavor.
A great dish for company or a holiday dinner!

title: meat stuffed manicotti
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet.
Add spinach, onion, salt, oregano and meat.
Mix well.
Cook until meat is no longer pink.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Add bread crumbs, egg and 2 tbsp. tomato paste.
Mix well.
Stuff manicotti with mixture.
Put in a greased baking dish, side by side.
Spread butter over stuffed manicotti. Spread tomato paste over manicotti.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Pour tomato sauce over.
Sprinkle mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 425° for 15 minutes or until mozzarella cheese melts.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Boil all ingredients together for 1 minute; then add broken, quartered soda crackers and boil 1 more minute.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake as regular apple pie.

title: blue soup
directions: Parboil and fry salt pork in heavy skillet.
Put in large pot with beans, peas, corn and water.
Bring to boil; lower heat to medium and boil 3 hours, adding more water as needed.
Mix corn meal and salt with enough water to make it soupy.
Add to pot and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes longer.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt oleo and mix with flour. Press into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Press pecans into crust and bake until light tan at 300°. Cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots into slices and cook until tender.
Cut onions and green peppers into thin slices.
Heat other ingredients.
Combine cooked carrots, onions and green peppers; pour heated mixture over and refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve cold.

title: squash souffle
directions: Drain squash in large bowl, mash.
Combine milk, bread crumbs and bacon drippings.
Add to squash.
Add eggs, cheese, onion, and baking powder.
Pour into rectangular baking dish.
Soak cracker crumbs in melted oleo.
Sprinkle on top of souffle.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 10-12 servings.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, salt and onions and let stand 2 hours.
Make a syrup of the sugar and vinegar by boiling this mixture only until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from stove.
When cool, set aside in refrigerator.
Drain the cucumbers and onions.
Squeeze all the water out.
Pack in plastic containers.
Pour the cold mixture over the pickles.
Cover tightly with lid and freeze.
Can be eaten in 2 or 3 weeks.
Do not fill containers too full.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise together until real fluffy. Add cranberry sauce, drained pineapple and pecans.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into large mold or in individual muffin tins or in a deep dish. Freeze until firm.

title: marinated slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine cabbage, pimientos, green pepper and onion.
Toss and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, simmer uncovered 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: angel muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Melt butter.
Combine butter with biscuit mix and sour cream.
Pour batter into muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Mix fresh and frozen thawed strawberries and let sit in fridge for 2 hours.
Bake cake in 3 layers.
Put berries and whipped cream on each layer and then cover with whipped cream.

title: mild chili con carne for a crowd
directions: Season ground meat with salt.
Brown in a 10-quart kettle. Add onions and green peppers and cook until tender, but not brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add water as needed for consistency. Makes about 25 cups.
This is good for everyone and easy on their stomachs.
Excellent on hot dogs.

title: red velvet delight
directions: Empty cake mix and cocoa into bowl. Stir to prevent lumps. Add all other ingredients and mix on low speed for a few seconds and beat 3 minutes on high with electric mixer.

title: jims biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add shortening, yeast and buttermilk to dry mix and knead well.
Flour as needed to roll out.
Roll out, cut and place biscuits in a greased pan.
Bake in a 425° preheated oven until brown (12 to 15 minutes).
Mix makes about 24 large biscuits.

title: smoked beef dip
directions: Soak onion in sherry until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix all together; add ice if needed.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash and quarter apples.
Remove spots and core.
Do not peel. Put apples in large roaster and add sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Combine sugar, 1 cup water, salt and spices in a large container.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer.
Combine cranberry sauce and 3 1/2 cups water; mix well.
Add to sugar syrup with apple juice.
Heat to just below simmering.
Pour hot punch in mugs or cups and dot with a bit of butter.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix, by hand, all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish (I spray with Pam).
Top casserole with small amount of seasoned stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: steak fajitas
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Quick fry until done.
Spread flour tortilla with Ranch dressing fill with steak and top with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and top with salsa.
Fold and eat like a taco.

title: suzy's chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces (size of a finger).
Rub with salt and pepper.

title: potato dish
directions: Mix water and dressing together.
Pour over potatoes in baking dish.
Pour melted butter over top.
Cook for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti with mussels, scallops and fish
directions: To make sauce, heat oil, add garlic and saute for about 30 seconds.
Stir
in	wine, basil, parsley and marjoram; cook about 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and boil 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add mussels.
Cover
and
cook	approximately
minutes, until shells open.
Add scallops and fish, cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer
until
scallops
and
fish	are barely firm. Season with salt
and
pepper.	Keep
warm.
Cook spaghetti al dente.
Drain. Pour
sauce
and
seafood over spaghetti, toss gently and serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients; add dry ingredients and mix well. Add raisins, nuts or coconut, if desired.
Using a teaspoon, drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: summer shells
directions: Cool and carefully separate shells.
Fill each shell with egg or tuna salad.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Serve with pickles, sliced cucumbers and tomatoes for a great summer supper (or snacks or lunch)!

title: cheese crisp
directions: Mix. Form into small balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: veal boursin
directions: Season veal scallops with salt, pepper and garlic powder and dust with flour.
Place 1 ounce Boursin on each scallop and roll up.
Spiral 1 slice of bacon around each scallop and fasten with a toothpick.
Saute scallops for several minutes on each side; when bacon is crisp, scallops are done.
Do not overcook.
Cheese will be softened.
Serve at once!
Marvelous with mushrooms sauteed in butter.
Serves 4.

title: gooey bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Combine yellow cake mix, eggs and butter in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Press, using your hands, into greased pans.
Combine confectioners sugar, cream cheese and vanilla extract in mixing bowl.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Spread over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: herbed nuts
directions: Place olive oil in a shallow baking pan.
Add nuts and toss them in oil until coated.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Toast in oven at 300° for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Do not scorch the nuts.
The nuts will keep cooking after being removed from oven, so do not overcook.

title: low cholesterol eggless chocolate layer cake
directions: Combine in a large bowl the flour, soda, salt, sugar and cocoa. Combine wet ingredients (water, oil, lemon juice and vanilla).
Pour wet ingredients in bowl containing the dry ingredients and mix well with fork (100 strokes).
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pans.
When cool, frost with Chocolate Buttercream Icing or your favorite frosting and decorate with drained, canned mandarin oranges.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Bring water to a boil in the bottom of a steamer.
Fit the basket into the steamer. Steam the asparagus over medium-high heat for about 6 minutes until bright green and tender.

Remove the steamer from the heat and let asparagus cool. Combine the yogurt and Blue cheese in a small saucepan. Warm over low heat for 1 to 2 minutes, whisking constantly, until the Blue cheese has melted. Remove the pan from the heat and whisk in the lemon juice, chives and garlic. Arrange the asparagus in the center of a serving plate and ring with tomato wedges. Drizzle the yogurt dressing over asparagus.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and garnish with fennel leaves.
Fat per serving:
0.9 grams.
Calories per serving:

title: hawaiian pumpkin pie
directions: Spread slightly softened ice cream in bottom of cool pie shell.
Place in freezer.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, spices and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over ice cream in pie; wrap, seal, label and date after you sprinkle with pecans.
When frozen, approximately 1 month.

title: party sherbet punch
directions: Put 1/2 of each flavor sherbet into punch bowl.
Add 1/2 can pineapple juice.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet to fill bowl.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugars, egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Form into balls; press down with a fork. Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: smothered spareribs
directions: Combine flour, salt, garlic powder, onion powder, pepper and red pepper in a pan.
Mix well.
Cut ribs into serving size; wash and pat dry on paper towel.
Set aside in large skillet.
Add oil over medium heat.
Dredge ribs in flour mixture.
Place ribs in hot oil and brown real well on all sides.
Remove ribs.
Pour out most of oil.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper; fry for about 5 minutes.
Place ribs in skillet; add water.
Cover and cook on low heat.
Add Kitchen Bouquet and more seasonings; cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pirate's punch
directions: Put fruit punch and ginger ale in refrigerator to chill.
Mix lemonade with water.
Add fruit punch and ginger ale.
Pour over ice cubes in a punch bowl.
Float lemon slices on top.
Makes 16 servings.

title: american spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package; drain.
Add tomato paste, water, onion salt and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and well blended.

title: crab stew-woo la-la
directions: Combine all ingredients in large, heavy pot.
Simmer on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: "chicken-chicken casserole"
directions: Boil chicken and cool.
Remove meat from bone; set aside.
In a large bowl add both cream of chicken soups, 1 1/2 cans of broth and 1 1/2 cans of milk.
Stir altogether and then add stuffing and then chicken.
Mix well together.
Put into 13 x 9 x 2-inch and round pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Grease pan or use Pam. You may put pats of butter on top before baking.)

title: honey muffins
directions: Combine honey, orange juice, butter, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.

title: fudge
directions: In large heavy pot, smear cocoa into sugar.
Add salt.
Add milk; stir until blended.
Over medium heat, bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Lower heat; let mixture boil.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; set until firm.
Beat together remainder of ingredients and put on top.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beets, in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; add beets.
Turn of heat.
Allow to stand overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together in food
processor until smooth.
Serve with Wheat Thins or similar snack crackers.

title: granola(honey)
directions: *If you desire peanut butter, maple or anything else, divide the measure in half, i.e., 1 2/3 cups honey, 1 2/3 cups peanut butter, etc.

title: spinach treat
directions: Heat cream cheese, margarine, salt, Tabasco sauce and milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add spinach; heat.
Top with egg.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain 20 ounces spaghetti.
Mix all together.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Plan to begin recipe the day before your special dinner. Dissolve yeast in 3 Tbsp. warm water.
Mix sugar, shortening, water, salt and eggs.
Stir in yeast and flour.
Knead thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough in half and roll out into a big circle.
Brush with 1/2 of the melted butter.
Cut into 16 pizza-like wedges.
Roll each wedge from large end to point like a crescent roll.
Place onto a greased baking sheet or seasoned stone.
Do the same to the other half of the dough. Allow 32 rolls to rise for about 2 hours in a warm place until doubled in size.
Bake until golden brown at 350°, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Combine milk and corn in heavy saucepan and simmer over medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring at intervals to prevent sticking. Place egg yolks, milk, sugar, salt and flour in blender and blend at medium for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add small bit of hot mixture to blender and whirl again.
Gradually add blender mixture to hot mixture and continue simmering 15 minutes.
Add butter and dash of pepper.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine the two mixtures together, adding sour milk alternately with flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: snicker cookies
directions: Melt Snicker bars in a pan.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Pour batter into melted Snicker bars and mix together. Place them in cookie pan and bake at 350°, checking occasionally.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Drain excess fat.
Add the salsa and simmer.
Remove from heat.
Spread cream cheese on a pie plate.
Pour cooled meat and salsa mixture over it.
Sprinkle with green pepper and shredded cheese.
Heat in microwave to melt cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken breasts in melted margarine. Roll in crushed saltines. Sprinkle with garlic salt, Parmesan and parsley flakes. Place in 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: skillet apple and pork
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook pork until brown on all sides.
Remove, set aside and spoon off all fat.
In same skillet, combine soup, apple juice, celery, onion, caraway seed, pepper and apple.
Heat to boiling.
Return pork to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 20 minutes or until pork is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Remove pork from skillet and slice.
Serve with sauce and pasta.
Garnish with celery leaves and additional apple slices.

title: salsa mexicana
directions: In a bowl, stir together the tomatoes, onion, chilies, cilantro, garlic salt and lime juice.
Let stand for 1 hour to blend flavors before serving.
Salsa can be stored for up to 1 week in refrigerator.

title: marvelous fresh strawberry pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, water and cornstarch over medium heat.
Stir until clear and thickened.
Add gelatin.
Let mixture cool.
Add strawberries to cooled gelatin mixture.
Pour strawberry filling into baked pie shells.
Chill pies until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream if desired. Yield:
2 pies. Enjoy.

title: clam fritters(appetizer)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shortening; beat until well blended and smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Melt shortening until it is 1/2-inch deep in a large skillet.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot shortening.
Fry until golden brown; turn and brown on the other side.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve at once.
Makes about 36 small appetizer fritters.

title: june's calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Put beans, meat mixture, catsup, brown sugar and vinegar in bean pot or covered casserole. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
If using crock-pot, cook 5 or 6 hours at 300°.

title: cinnamon swirl date ring
directions: Combine biscuit mix and sugar in mixing bowl; cut in butter until mixture resembles rice kernels.
Gently stir in milk just until ingredients are moistened.
Drop half of dough by tablespoonfuls into a greased 6-cup ring mold.
Sprinkle with Cinnamon-Date Filling.
Top with remaining dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Invert mold onto plate.
Leave over cake 5 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes one coffee ring.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Delicious on gingerbread.

title: banana split squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until golden at 375° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs, confectioners sugar, 2 sticks margarine and vanilla.
Spread over crust.
Spread with drained pineapple next.
Place sliced bananas on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an uncooked pie shell. Cook for 45 minutes on 350°. Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper. Cook in a saute pan until done (about 7 minutes each side). Mix slaw dressing, celery, grapes, apple and cashews. When chicken is cooled, dice into 1/4-inch pieces and add to dressing mixture. Serve as a salad on lettuce leaves or on a croissant roll. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and margarine.
Stir in milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: corn mexicaine
directions: Combine peppers and butter and cook, covered, 3 minutes.
Add corn, salt and pepper.
Stir; heat through.
Serves 4.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasonings; mix well.
Chill until stiff. Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.
(Leftover cheese ball can be re-shaped and refrigerated.
Will keep up to one week.)

title: mandelkrantz
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in warm water in a small bowl; let stand 5 minutes.

title: carol's hot curried fruit compote(best made the day before serving)
directions: Drain all fruits and place all but cherries in 2-quart casserole.
Add nuts.
Melt butter; blend in sugar, curry powder, cinnamon and spoon over fruit.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Add cherries; bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve warm.

title: gloria's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; reserve broth.
Cool chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Cook noodles in broth with added water.
Combine soups and sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, drained noodles, mushrooms and pimiento.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab souffle
directions: Cube 4 slices bread; put in long 3-quart glass casserole. Combine next 5 ingredients; spread over bread cubes.
Cube other 4 slices of bread over this.
Beat eggs; add milk and pour over mixture.
This may be refrigerated until the next day.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then spoon soup and cheese over and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake an additional 60 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant-zucchini parmigiana
directions: For tomato sauce, in medium saucepan combine broth, celery, onion and garlic.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, rosemary and pepper.
Return mixture to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients to boiling, stirring continuously. Cool.
Pour over berries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.
Makes 2 deep-dish pies.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer everything in a 1 or 2-quart casserole with buttered crumbs on top and bottom.
On bottom, put 1/2 buttered bread crumbs, next corned beef, next sauerkraut, next mayo and Thousand Island dressing, mixed, next Swiss cheese and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Add tomatoes, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: one dish meal in foil
directions: Place all ingredients in a 12-inch square of foil, shiny side up.
Fold foil over vegetables and seal package.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 serving.

title: instant potato casserole
directions: Fold ingredients into potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grape pie
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 350°.

title: mashed potato donuts
directions: Beat well with mixer first 6 ingredients.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Roll on floured board and cut.
Fry until brown.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu(yields 4 breasts)
directions: Brown chicken breasts (both sides) in skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay browned chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Lay 2 ham slices on open breasts.
Top with 1 Swiss cheese slice (on top of ham).
Fold breasts.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Put 1 slice Swiss cheese on top of each folded breast.
Pour jar of gravy over all 4.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until done.

title: garlic crescent rolls
directions: Separate roll dough into four triangles.
Sprinkle with cheese and garlic powder.
Beginning at the wide end, roll up dough. Place with point down on a greased baking sheet.
Brush with egg, sprinkle with seeds.
Bake at 375 degrees for 11-13 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook at 250° for 1 hour.
Cover cookie sheet with brown paper.
Cool completely.

title: date pecan cake
directions: Cut dates.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar and then sift over dates, pecans, coconut and raisins.
Melt butter and add with vanilla.
Mix.
Beat egg yolks until creamy smooth and add.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in very gently.
Pour into a greased and lined tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pear soup(servings:  6)
directions: Put pears in food processor until smooth.
Saute onion in butter and add to pear mixture.
Add pumpkin and process until smooth.
Transfer pumpkin mixture to a large saucepan.
Add chicken broth and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Stir in cream and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
May garnish with a small dob of sour cream and a strip of green onion.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9 x 12-inch buttered dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Dribble 1/2 cup melted butter over the top of cornflakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not cover.

title: mama's pie crust
directions: Mix or cream together the flour, lard, sugar and salt.
Slowly add water. Work the dough after adding water as little as possible. Form a big ball.
Divide in half.
Place on floured board and roll out to fit size of pie pan.
Bake.
Makes 2 crusts or 1 cobbler crust.

title: gazpacho
directions: Peel the tomatoes and quarter them; remove seeds.
In food processor or blender, combine half of the tomatoes, onion, cucumber, green and red peppers and all of the garlic and half of the tomato juice.
Process until smooth.
Process the remaining ingredients.
Add to the first mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours. Serve in chilled bowls.
May garnish with croutons.
Yields 6 cups.

title: uncooked oatmeal-chocolate cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan, then add sweet milk, cocoa and sugar.
Bring this to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute. Remove from fire and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper until hard.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Dilute all juices according to instructions on cans and combine.
Crush frozen raspberries.
Freeze 1/3 amount of raspberries to use in place of ice.
Mix remaining raspberries with juices.
This makes 8 quarts of punch.

title: pecan torte
directions: Slowly mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream of ice cream.

title: summer lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add boiling water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup of liquid. Pour over gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Add marshmallows and stir slightly.
Cool until mixture starts to thicken.
Add pineapple and nut meats.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into a 5 cup mold.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute onions until tender.
Put aside; cook livers covered in a small amount of butter, stirring occasionally, until no longer pink.
Put livers and onions through a meat grinder; blend with remaining ingredients.
Place mixture in a 2-cup mold.
Chill several hours; carefully unmold.
Serve with crackers.

title: diet center mayonnaise
directions: Place all ingredients except
oil
in a blender.
Blend at high speed for 5 seconds.
Add
the
oil in a small stream. If the mayonnaise becomes too thick to blend as you are adding the last of the oil, put in a few extra drops vinegar or lemon juice. Store in covered container up to a week.

title: pineapple sheet cake and icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased and floured sheet cake pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: curried chicken casserole
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cook the Rice-A-Roni.
Add curry powder while cooking.
Drain broccoli.
Cook and cut up chicken.
Mix the milk and mayonnaise with the cream of chicken soup; pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cheese in bowl with fork.
Beat cream until stiff in separate bowl.
Add all ingredients in with cheese and beat.
Mix well and add whipped cream.

title: easy bake chicken
directions: Spray 2-quart oblong baking dish with vegetable cooking spray. Arrange chicken, bone side down, in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: spuds
directions: Scrub taters well and slice into 1/4-inch thick slices. Spread out on a lightly sprayed cookie sheet; overlapping slightly to fit on cookie sheet may be necessary.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until tender.
Place taters on a microwavable serving plate and top with cheese.
Microwave on High until cheese is melted.
Serve with Ranch dressing.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Spread oleo in large oblong pan, leaving some in chunks.
Mix soups and rice together.
Pour in pan.
Lay chicken over rice skin side up.
Push chicken down in mixture.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake 2 hours at 350°, uncovered.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Beat pudding and cold milk together well.
Add sour cream and orange juice concentrate.
Beat until well blended.
Refrigerate and serve with fresh fruit.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries in food chopper; add sugar and stir well. Leave overnight.
Add pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
A wonderful holiday dish.

title: salt water taffy(yields 50 to 60 pieces)
directions: Combine sugar with cornstarch, corn syrup, water, salt and margarine in a heavy gauge saucepan.
Stir well to blend.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Cover saucepan and bring to a boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Uncover and place a candy thermometer in the pan.
Boil mixture, without stirring, until a hard ball will form when dropped into cold water, about 260° to 265° on the candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add flavoring oil and food coloring.
Stir gently; pour on greased marble slab or shallow greased pan to cool.
When cool enough to handle, grease hands and pull until candy is light in color and has a satiny color (glass).
Pull into long ropes; cut with scissors into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap each piece in wax paper, twisting ends.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine milk and soda and set aside.
Combine other ingredients.
Combine water, cocoa and butter in saucepan and bring to boil.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add eggs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 can milk.
Combine rest of ingredients (except chocolate chips) in cake mix.
Pour 3/4 into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Will be thick.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Pour caramel on top.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pinch rest of dough on top and bake 20 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix. Serve with all kinds of fruit or wafer cookies.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots in unsalted water until tender. Drain; place in bowl.
Add onion and green pepper.
Make a sauce with sugar, oil, mustard, vinegar, salt and tomato soup.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon pepper and pour over carrots.
Let marinate; keep refrigerated.

title: mexican vegetable soup
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, brown the ground beef; drain.
Add the taco seasoning mix, tomato juice, chili beans, frozen vegetables and tomato paste.
Bring just to a boil.
Reduce the heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until veggies are tender, stirring occasionally.
Top each serving with corn chips and Cheddar cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 large servings or 10 to 12 little ones.

title: microwave hot broccoli dip
directions: Remove outer wrap of frozen broccoli and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Microwave onion and celery in butter 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Add soup and cheese.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: boned chicken casserole
directions: Mix all this together.
Put in buttered dish and bake 30 minutes in a 450° oven.
Last 5 minutes, put crumbled potato chips on top.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll into ball. Save some chipped beef and scallion for outside of cheese ball.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Add low-fat milk to fill line of ice cream freezer.
Use gallon size freezer.
If you use a 2-quart freezer only use 2 cans of evaporated milk and 1 can Eagle Brand milk.
Freeze as usual.

title: grits and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix grits, milk, broccoli and oleo.
Top with cheese.
Bake to melt cheese.

title: french carrots
directions: Scrape, rinse and dry carrots.
Cut into slices or quarters. Cook in saucepan with enough liquid to cover.
Season with salt, pepper, sugar and butter.
Bring to a boil and simmer covered until all liquid is cooked away and the carrots are evenly glazed. Sprinkle with minced parsley.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in a double boiler.
Chill until completely cool and thickened.

title: hormel ham dip
directions: Put all ingredients in the food processor.
Serve with crackers.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine candy bars and butter in heavy saucepan; cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly. Combine sugar and shortening; beat until creamy. Add eggs and continue beating until light and fluffy. Combine flour and salt; combine buttermilk and soda. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla and candy bar mixture. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tested done.

title: italian oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a baking sheet with foil and lightly grease the foil.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2-inch thick wedges.
Melt the butter on the stove top or microwave.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine cream cheese, nuts and garlic.
Add a small amount of mayonnaise.
Do not get mixture too thin.
Spread each side of slice of ham with mixture; roll as for jelly roll.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into slices.
Serve each slice on round cracker, if desired.

title: easy bread and butter pickles(canning recipe)
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, green peppers and whole garlic. Add salt.
Mix well and cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly. Let stand 3 hours.
Add ice, if needed.
Drain well.
Remove garlic.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters. Pat dry with paper towels. Arrange oysters in 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Top with layers of green onion, 1 cup parsley and cracker crumbs. Combine next 4 ingredients, mixing well. Pour evenly over cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yield: 12 servings.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Brown ground chuck, stirring to a crumble; drain well.
Wipe skillet out with paper towel.
Return meat to skillet.
Layer potatoes, carrots, onion, green pepper and tomatoes over top. Sprinkle with pepper and salt.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top if desired.

title: grace's barbecue sauce
directions: Brown meat with onion and celery.
Drain well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: bibingka mochiko
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wordy derd dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl; cover and put in refrigerator to cool.
Great with chips and vegetables.
Enjoy!

title: deluxe low-fat chicken burritos
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Set aside.
In a large nonstick skillet, place chicken, taco seasoning and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Stir in salsa and black olives.
Heat tortillas according to package. Keep well covered, until used.
Divide and spoon refried beans onto tortillas.
Top with chicken, cheese, lettuce and tomato.
