Fold or roll up and serve immediately.
Makes 10 burritos.

title: chicken slop
directions: Mix everything together and pour into greased baking dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: mrs. gillis strawberry jello salad
directions: Cook the Jell-O, water and crushed pineapple. Cool. Add cottage cheese, sour cream and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1-quart casserole dish.
Put raisins in a small microwave-proof bowl; add a little water. Microwave on High for 50 to 60 seconds; set aside.
In a medium bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add raisins and water, rice, vanilla, sugar and milk.
Stir thoroughly.
Add enough additional milk to make mixture loose.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in water bath for about 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grate entire orange (including peel) in a food processor until finely chopped.
Add apple and continue grating, then add cranberries.
Grate until a chunky sauce forms.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cheese and powdered sugar; fold in Dream Whip after beating. Pour over crumbs and top with cherries.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, combine butter, oil, water and cocoa.
Cook, stirring to blend, and bring to a boil.
Stir in flour mixture.
Stir soda into buttermilk and add with eggs and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine okra, onion, salt, pepper, water and egg; mix well. In another bowl, combine flour, corn meal and baking powder, add to okra mixture.
Form into patties about the size of a silver dollar and fry in just enough shortening to keep from sticking.

title: easy blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk, egg and butter to dry mix.
Stir until moist.
Add blueberries.
Spoon batter into 12 to 15 paper-lined or greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar; save 1/2 of this mixture.
Put other 1/2 in large bowl with lid.
Cut dough into quarters.
Put 1/2 into bowl with lid and shake.
Put pieces in buttered Bundt pan. Do the same with second half of dough.
Melt margarine over low heat and add saved sugar mixture .
Cook for a few minutes, then pour over dough.
Bake in 375°
oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Invert on plate and remove Bundt pan.
Let cool.
Just pull a piece off with fingers.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Wash, peel and dice potatoes. Boil in lightly salted water until done.
Drain potatoes and put in a slightly greased casserole dish.
Melt margarine in a double boiler.
Add flour and evaporated milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Add salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: In large bowl, add 2 cups of the flour, sugar, salt and warm oil, blending well.
Stir in the hot water and yeast and beat with a spoon until mixture is smooth and satiny.
Slowly add 3 cups more flour, mixing until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Cover with warm wet dish towel and let stand for 10 minutes.

If you do not have dough hooks on your mixer to knead dough for 10 to 15 minutes until smooth and satiny, then knead the dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth and satiny, for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Place the kneaded dough into the lightly greased bread pans to rise in a warm place for about 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until loaves sound hollow when tapped and are golden in color.
Remove from pans immediately.
Then brush tops with melted butter.

title: chicken fried rabbit with cream gravy
directions: Shake rabbit in a paper bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Heat a heavy skillet with lid that will just hold the rabbit pieces. Add lard or oil, turn heat to medium, add rabbit and brown on all sides.
Add more fat, if needed.

title: crispy cocoa bars
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in cocoa and marshmallows.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth and well blended.
Continue cooking and stirring for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into prepared pan.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 24 bars.

title: beef sandwich filling
directions: Mix all ingredients and place on favorite bread.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of filling (4 sandwiches).

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon. Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and freeze until firm. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before cutting into squares. Serve on lettuce leaves and return any leftovers to freezer. Serves 15.

title: venison stew
directions: Mix flour with water until lumps are gone.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 7 hours or until ingredients are tender.

title: irish cream
directions: Put in blender (1/2 at a time if too much for your blender).

title: marshmallow roll
directions: Use small marshmallows or cut large ones in quarters, put in a bowl and add water.
Add Eagle Brand condensed milk, nuts and dates; blend well.
Add cracker crumbs and blend well.
Form into small balls about the size of a walnut.
Roll each in cracker crumbs.
Chill before serving.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add flavorings.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat the 1 egg and mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the next 2 eggs and mix with confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over cake layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Needs no icing.
Serves 24.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove from tins immediately and cool on racks.
Makes 20 to 24.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased dish approximately 1 hour at 375°.

title: hot off the grill ham steaks
directions: Combine sugar, horseradish and lemon juice; boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Brush on ham steaks and grill.
Watch carefully, they burn easily.
Tasty!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven
to
Brown beef and onion. Add taco sauce and
water.
Cook
according
to
directions.
Reserve. Spray an 11	x
x 2-inch dish or pan.
Layer refried beans, taco mixture and olives. Bake for 30 minutes. Top with cheese. Pop in
oven until cheese melts.
Garnish with Doritos, tomatoes, lettuce and sour cream.

title: stuffed tomatoes(serves 6)
directions: Cook pasta until done but firm.
Rinse and pour into bowl. Stir in eggs, celery, scallions and enough yogurt or mayo to make a creamy mixture. Season to taste with salt.

title: potatoes on the grill
directions: Slice potatoes and onion.
Cut 2 pieces of foil 16-inches long.
Spread small amount of butter on bottom piece of foil. Layer onion and potatoes.
Have onion in top and bottom layers. Slice remaining butter and dot across top.
Cover with foil.
Fold edges in several times to seal.
Bake over indirect heat on grill for 30 minutes.
Turn halfway through.
(My grill controls are high and low; use high with the package over the center.

title: radish mice
directions: Cut off the rounded bottom of a radish so that it is flat on the bottom.
Make two slits on the radish.
Cut the piece that you cut off in half.
Stick the pieces in the slits for ears.
Poke holes for eyes.
Make a slit for a mouth.

title: chocolate chip milkshake
directions: Place milk, ice cream and vanilla in blender.
Blend on high speed for 3 seconds.
Stir.
Blend on low speed until smooth or about 5 seconds.
Add chocolate chips and blend on low speed 3 seconds.
Makes 2 servings, 1 cup each.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain spinach well and squeeze to remove excess moisture. Combine spinach with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
These can be made ahead and frozen and then baked.
Can be made in blender. Taste like they are made with sausage.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 100.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, honey and lemon juice.
Add poppy seed as desired.
Serve over fruit.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: In a large plastic bag, mix all dry ingredients.
Remove skin from chicken and coat chicken by shaking a piece at a time in bag. Put chicken in a roasting pan that has been coated with oil. Drizzle melted butter over chicken pieces.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for about 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool right side up for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: aunt roma's parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bag. Moisten potatoes in water and shake in bag to coat. Melt butter in a baking dish; place potatoes in a single layer. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Turn after 30 minutes. Remove cover at end to brown.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: butter frosting
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add milk and confectioners sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing constantly.
Add 1 tablespoon milk and more if needed.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Mix all together; roll out and cut in circles.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
After cooled, dip in chocolate with paraffin and put on wax paper.
Return to refrigerator to cool.
Enjoy.

title: apple caramel cake
directions: Beat well in large bowl, oil, sugar and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan for 50 to 55 minutes.
Glaze.

title: caramel cashew crunch squares
directions: Melt butter, water and caramels together in microwave. Add Cocoa Krispies and cashews. Mix all together. Wait 1 minute, then add chips. Press in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cool and cut into squares.

title: donna's baked bean chili
directions: Mix together ground beef and soup mix.
Brown and drain. Combine all ingredients and slow cook in a crock-pot.

title: breakfast before
directions: Heat oven to 350° or 325° if using a glass baking dish.
Saute sausage; drain well.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish:
first cubed bread, second add sausage and third cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Do not stir!
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove dish from refrigerator for 30 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: quick baked beans
directions: In skillet, fry finely chopped bacon, onion, pepper and celery; brown.
Add beans (canned), sugar, dash of catsup and tomato paste. Put into casserole; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linguine with cauliflower
directions: Add cauliflower, olive oil, garlic and butter to large skillet.
Brown cauliflower over medium heat until browned on same sides but still a bit crisp.
Place cauliflower in bowl; set aside.
Add onions to skillet and more oil if needed.
Cook until wilted and slightly browned.
Add tomatoes to onions.
Heat.
Add cauliflower, salt, pepper and red pepper to taste.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Do not overcook!
Cook linguine.
Add to skillet or put into large bowl with cauliflower mixture and toss.
Serves 6. Pass the cheese.

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl. Add eggs; beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended. Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan. Cool in pan. Frost if desired cut into squares. 16 brownies.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, together in bowl.
Crumble bread up in baking dish and pour mixture over bread.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out and cool or eat warm, if desired.

title: shanty bean soup
directions: Soak limas overnight and drain.
Add fresh water to cover beans.
Cook until soft.
Add ingredients; simmer all day.
(Must be sweet enough.)

title: club sandwiches
directions: Toast bread.
Spread with mayonnaise.
Place 2 slices turkey, 1 slice tomato, 3 slices bacon and 2 lettuce leaves on each of 6 slices toast.
Cover with remaining toast; cut diagonally into fourths.
Serves 6.

title: chicken wellington
directions: Poaching Liquid:
In a wide frying pan, combine water, white wine, carrot, onion, bay leaf, black peppers, allspice, salt, thyme leaves and parsley.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Lay chicken pieces in poaching liquid.
Cover and gently simmer until chicken is just pink in center (cut gash to test), about 7 to 10 minutes.
With a slotted spatula, lift chicken from pan.
Cool, then cover and chill.
Reserve poaching liquid.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and butter in large bowl, stir until blended.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Divide into two portions. Roll out one portion on floured surface, spread with 1/2 sausage and roll up.
Repeat with second portion.
Place in freezer until hard enough to slice.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until well mixed.
Add sugar that has been mixed with flour (to avoid lumps).
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 400° approximately one hour or until firm in center.

title: apple dip
directions: Soak sliced apples in 2 cups water, 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1 tablespoon salt; cover.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until blended.
Place on serving dish.
Top with caramel and nuts.
Pat apples dry and arrange around dip.

title: walnut custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add beaten eggs.
Add molasses, water and chopped nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and top with strips.
Bake at 325° until set good and crust is light brown.

title: texas con queso dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook for at least 1 hour.
Keep hot and serve with tortilla chips.

title: nettie craig's crunchy chip squares
directions: Mix. Drop by spoonfuls and spread with a fork.
Bake at 350° until when pressed with finger dents lightly.
M-m-good.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Heat and stir first 3 ingredients together until sugar is melted.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Uncover and cook until hard stage is reached when dropped in cold water.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, water and oil.
Add dry ingredients; mix well, while adding apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix or toss ingredients.
Makes great snack crackers or use as croutons.

title: mock pink champagne
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Stir in cranberry, pineapple and orange juices.
Chill.
Just before serving add the Sprite or 7-Up.
I always double this recipe several times if we are having guests.

title: corn muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add cornmeal, stirring only enough to mix.
Fill 2/3 full and bake 25 minutes at 425°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: zesty beef enchiladas(with variations)
directions: In a skillet, cook beef until no longer pink; drain.
Stir in 1/2 c. sauce and 1 c. cheese.
Warm tortillas according to package directions.
Spread 1/2 c. sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Spoon about 2 tablespoons meat mixture down the center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam-side down in baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield: 10-12 enchiladas.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1/3 cup sugar with cornstarch and salt.
Blend in milk, then egg yolks.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Don't overcook.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
In pastry shell, alternate layers of banana slices and cream filling. Cover and chill.
Top with whipped cream and extra banana slices. For a quick and good garnish, use a whipped topping.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut vegetables into 4-quart pan.
Measure 7 cups of water. Bring to a boil.
Add dry soup mix. Stir; cover with heat lowered and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown
meat with onion.
Add spices.
Drain.
Combine tomato sauce, paste and one cup of water.
Add spice to taste and boil. Combine with meat.
Cook noodles, drain and run cold water over them.

title: orange butter
directions: Whip the orange peel, butter and cream cheese.
Stir in orange pieces and honey.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes the equivalent of 1 pound of butter or margarine.

title: dutch apple cake in microwave
directions: Use an angel food cake pan.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into pan.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes in microwave.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: shipwreck
directions: Cook onion and meat until brown.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix with all ingredients.
Spread grated cheese on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: feta cheese and spinach chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut spinach into Feta cheese.
Place cheese and spinach mixture in center of chicken breast.
Fold sides of chicken to overlap.
Place fold down in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Put 1/4 tablespoon butter on each breast.
Bake for 30 minutes. Baste once or twice before baking.

title: cuban custard
directions: Cook slowly, stirring it almost constantly until it thickens. Spray on top ground cinnamon.

title: chicken or pork chow mein
directions: In large frypan, cook chicken or pork in small amount of oil or spray, about 1/2 hour.
Add cut up celery and onions with liquid from one can of sprouts; cook about 15 minutes.
Add sprouts and cook about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch in other liquid from bean sprouts.
Add to chow mein mixture and cook until thickened.
Serve with rice and chow mein noodles.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Gradually beat in flour.
Then add chips and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: chicken breasts en casserole with chipped beef(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Bone and skin chicken breasts.
Line casserole with chipped beef.
Roll a slice of bacon around each chicken breast and put into casserole on top of the chipped beef.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Spoon over chicken pieces.
Bake in uncovered casserole at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Very good for dinner party.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour (about 1/2 cup at a time). Add flavorings.

title: truffles
directions: Mix sugar and milk in saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir in morsels and almond extract.
Chill 45 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll around in the nuts.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Make cake as to directions plus 3 tablespoons creme de menthe in 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Spread fudge over cake.
Mix 3 tablespoons of creme de menthe in Cool Whip, then frost cake.

title: fondant candy
directions: Mix all ingredients well and cook on low heat.
Cook for 1 hour, it will take 45 minutes for mixture to start boiling.
Test in cold water until mixture forms a soft ball by dropping a small amount in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla (1 teaspoon).
Sprinkle countertop with cold water and pour candy on the counter, a little at a time.
Move the mixture back and forth with a wooden spatula, until mixture is white in color, creamy and will become thick in consistency.
Refrigerate overnight, having made fondant into small balls (size of a piece of candy) using cornstarch on your hands.
Coat candy balls with melted sweetened chocolate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cook onions and celery in small amount of butter until tender.
Drain broccoli.
Mix celery, onions, Cheez Whiz and soup together.
Add rice and mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover.
Bake in oven at 350° until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: cheese ball recipe
directions: Let ingredients stand at room temperature until soft.
Mix on high until completely blended.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form into balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: granny's macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large pan, bring water, salt and oil to a rolling boil. Add macaroni (stir several times during cooking).
Boil until macaroni is tender (not mushy).
Drain.
Add oleo, cheese and soup.
Cover until melted.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until slightly brown around edges.

title: summer vegetable salad
directions: Can also use finely chopped bell pepper (if wanted) but do not blend.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend cake mix and jello. Add oil and milk; beat. Add one egg at a time and beat until all eggs are used and well beaten (about 4 minutes). Fold into the batter the coconut, berries and nuts. Pour into 3 cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: cheese vegetable chowder
directions: Place water, potatoes, carrots and celery in small saucepan. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook until vegetables are barely tender, about 12 minutes.
Reserve vegetables and cooking liquid. Saute onion in butter in small Dutch oven over medium heat until transparent, about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Cook and stir one minute.
Gradually whisk in stock, add milk and salt. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils for 1 minute.
Stir in cheese and baking soda.
Add reserved vegetables and cooking liquid.
Heat over medium heat just until soup is very hot.
Remove from heat, season to taste with pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Yields 8 (1-cup) servings.

title: plum good cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at one time with electric beater until eggs are well beaten.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Put oil in shallow baking pan.
Place sliced tomatoes and onions in oil and stir to coat with oil. Sprinkle with sugar, then a good layer of cheese.
Last add crumbs over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Melt margarine.
Pour over sugar.
Mix yeast, egg and add flour.
Fill muffin pan 2/3 full. Let rise and bake.

title: cheese spread
directions: Serve with crackers (whole wheat is best).

title: egg casserole
directions: Whip together eggs, salt, dry mustard and the half and half.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook together for approximately 15 minutes. When mixture starts to boil, seal in hot jars.

title: quick and easy ham and bean soup
directions: Put in large cooking pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook, covered, until vegetables are tender.
Can substitute canned vegetables instead of fresh.

title: punch for 100
directions: Dissolve sugar, jello and Kool-Aid in the boiling water.
Add 1 1/2 gallons cold water, plus juices.
Mix well.
Refrigerate. At serving time, add chilled ginger ale.

title: single layer chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Beat with wire whip.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
This is a very easy, moist and quick cake.

title: pecan goodies(a yummy christmas cookie)
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar.
Cream again.
Sift together dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten ball to 1/3-inch with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix together and put in Bundt pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: cucumber and celery pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and put in ice water until chilled.
Remove; cut in long strips.
Pack in jars with long strips of celery.
Drain water from jar.
Mix water, vinegar, sugar and salt and bring to boil.
Pour over cucumbers in jars.
Seal.
Leave rings on jars. Serve later.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Roll veal slices in flour, salt and pepper.
Heat Wesson oil in a large skillet; fry onion and green pepper until tender.
Remove. Add veal; brown both sides.
Pour off excess oil.
Add soup mixed with water.
Return the onion and green pepper.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat until melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and boil until thick.
Add butter after it thickens.
Pour into a prepared pie shell and let set.

title: hot fudge brownie sunday
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs, shortening, vanilla and chocolate (cocoa and oil mixed).
Stir in remaining ingredients of brownies excepting ice cream and fudge sauce.
Bake at 350 degrees until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan, about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool; cut into squares and top with scoop of ice cream and fudge sauce.

title: date loaf cake
directions: Combine raisins and dates in a bowl.
Mix soda and boiling water, then pour over dates and raisins.
Let sit until other ingredients are mixed.
Add raisins and dates to mixture.
Put in greased and floured Bundt pan or large pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Alternately add flour, baking powder and soda with sour cream.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon together for the cinnamon-sugar mix.
Butter and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Put 1/3 batter in pan.
Sprinkle half cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Pour rest of batter; sprinkle rest of cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan on cake rack for 15 minutes.
Remove; finish cooling on rack.

title: beef dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in deep casserole dish for 3 hours
in 300° oven.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and frost cake.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Beat brown sugar and oleo. Add egg and vanilla; mix thoroughly. Pour into tart shells. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Makes 24 tarts.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: To completely fill crock-pot, add tomato sauce or water, depending on consistency desired.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed and stir well one time.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 5 to 6 hours.
Hot and delicious.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine noodles with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover.
Cook on High in microwave for 10 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
If desired, sprinkle 3/4 cup crushed potato chips on top. Cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
(May bake in regular oven 25 minutes at 350°.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine the pretzels, margarine and sugar; lightly pat in a baking dish and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat the cream cheese, dry whipped topping and sugar together until smooth and creamy.
Spread over the cooled crust.
Mix together the gelatin, frozen strawberries and boiling water; set lightly and spread on top.
Refrigerate for two hours or overnight for best results.

title: mock corn bread
directions: Bake in greased and floured pan.

title: mom's snickerdoodles
directions: Cream all liquid ingredients. Add flour and cream of tartar. Drop by small balls onto greased cookie sheet.
Leave space enough to allow for spreading.

title: chicken recipe
directions: Saute onions and almonds in butter; mix in rest of ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Debone cooked chicken.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add white sauce, Rotel, soups, chicken and chili powder. Place 1/2 of the tortilla chips in a 10x13 pan.
Cover with 1/2 chicken mixture, 1/2 of the olives, and 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: nut goody bars
directions: Microwave to melt top
ingredients;	pour 1/2 of the ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate to set.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain, cook broccoli, drain and chop; set aside.
Meanwhile blend soups, parmesan cheese, sour cream, onion, beaten egg, garlic salt and pepper.
Crumble in bouillon cubes. Blend well.
Lightly spread a little mixture on baking dish.
Add chopped turkey mixture on baking dish.
Add chopped turkey to remaining mixture.
Put layer of noodles overlapping in dish. Spread with 1/3 turkey mixture, then 1/3 broccoli, mozzarella and sharp cheeses.
Repeat with 2 more layers, ending with cheeses, sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Combine and cook rhubarb, sugar and pineapple for 12 minutes. Add to mixture 1 box strawberry jello.
Put in jars.
Cool and freeze.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Add catsup to thin out mixture for hot dogs, then sprinkle chili powder to taste.
Keep warm in crock-pot or freeze for later use.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Slice cooked sweet potatoes into 1/2 inch slices.
In a large frying pan, melt butter blend in brown sugar.
Add vanilla and allspice.
Mix thoroughly.
Place potato slices in mixture and cook over medium heat until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Halve eggs and mash yolks with fork.
Mix them with butter, mayonnaise, onion, mustard, vinegar and seasonings.
Fill egg whites.
Garnish with a dab of mayonnaise and tiny sprig of parsley on top of each half.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, Eagle Brand milk and butter together (low heat).
Pour over marshmallows and nuts; stir.
Pour into wax-lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Remove from pan. Peel off paper.
Cut in squares.
Cover and store at room temperature or can freeze for later use.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix lemonade, limeade, orange juice and pineapple juice together.
Add 7-Up and sherbet the last minute or just before ready to serve.
This was served at our wedding in 1968.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Cream together salt, oleo, brown sugar and vanilla.
Combine mashed bananas, eggs and cocoa.
Mix all ingredients together and add nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
If desired, frost when cool.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: In a small saucepan, combine wine, oil, onion (thinly sliced and separated into rings), salt, parsley flakes, mustard and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add the drained mushroom crowns.
Simmer for 5 to 6 minutes.
Chill in a covered bowl several hours.
Stir several times.
Drain and serve with picks on your next party tray.

title: pasta e fagioli(pasta and beans)
directions: Add all ingredients except tubettini and olive oil.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Cook tubettini in salted water.
Drain. Add to beans and vegetables.
Sprinkle with grated Romano cheese.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and fruit with cream in a blender.
Pour into a freezer.
Add milk to 1-inch from the top.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: zucchini slice
directions: Grate unpeeled zucchini coarsely.
Grate carrots.
Chop onion. Combine zucchini, carrots, onion, cheese, flour, oil and lightly beaten eggs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until browned.

title: chocolate dessert(girdle buster)
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Pat and bake in 9 x 13-inch dish for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix eggs, one at a time, to oleo, sugar and coloring.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with cup of buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Mix ingredients and place chicken breasts on top.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on everything.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a large 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream sugar, oil, egg yolks, water, vanilla and lemon together.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar stiff; fold in cake.
Bake at 350° in tube pan for 35 to 50 minutes.
You can tell by looking at it when done.

title: "fast 'n fancy" macaroons
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon, 1 inch apart, onto well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove at once.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Add packages of vanilla pudding mix with juice from fruit cocktail.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Add fruit cocktail.
Mix well again.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Stir before serving.

title: drunken chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and brown it.
Put it in a roaster.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, ground sage, garlic powder, and hot pepper.
Add 8 oz. dry wine on the chicken, as much as desired but not too much. Let it simmer.
When it has simmered, take it out and put the tomatoes in.
Then add a can of water in the roaster.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 serve it.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg, vanilla, flour, baking powder and nuts; roll into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press flat with fork dipped in milk. Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter baking dish.
Mix apples, 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Blend flour and salt. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 45 minutes, until browned and bubbly and apples are tender.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake cake mix, according to directions.
Remove cake from oven.
Punch holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour thawed strawberries and syrup evenly on top.
In a medium size bowl with mixer, combine pudding mix, milk and cream cheese.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Spread this on top of strawberries.
Last, spread entire container of Cool Whip evenly across top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: all occasion punch
directions: Mix cold Hawaiian Punch and 7-Up.
Add lime-aid in large punch bowl.
Add large spoonfuls of sherbet and stir.

title: pumpkin-pecan bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Combine flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; mix well.
In medium bowl, combine oil, water, eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Add to flour mixture; beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Fold in pecans.
Pour batter into pans. Bake for 60 to 70 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mixed-up pizzaiola bake
directions: Optional toppings:
Sauteed thinly sliced Italian frying peppers, red onion, bell peppers or mushrooms, olives, cooked and crumbled Italian sausage, thinly sliced sun-dried tomatoes.

title: grandma's hot pickled okra
directions: Trim stems from okra.
Do not cut into pod.
Pack in 4 pint jars, add 1 tablespoon dill weed, 1 clove garlic, 2 hot peppers and a few green cherry tomatoes (whole) in each jar.
Mix salt, water and vinegar in saucepan, heat to boiling and pour in each jar; seal.
Let stand 3 weeks before serving.

title: meatball stuff and rice or pasta
directions: Mix meat, egg and bread; form into balls.
Brown in skillet. Remove from skillet and pour off grease.
Put sauce stuff (your own or Classico) in the skillet.
Use the Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Return the meatballs to the skillet and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
While you cook rice or noodles.
Stir the meatballs occasionally.
Before you serve, mix in 1/2 carton sour cream or more if you prefer.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: hobo stew
directions: Press hamburger in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cut up potatoes, carrots and onions over top of meat.
Add corn, soup, water and seasonings.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook sausage, ground chuck, onion and oregano until done. Then mix with tomato and cheese soups.
Cook noodles as directed on package and put in casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture over noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix 2 cups warm water, sugar, fruit, salt, oil, raisins, cinnamon and cloves together in a large saucepan and bring to hard boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool, then put nuts, baking soda, 1 teaspoon warm water and flour into fruit mixture and stir well. Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: Cut bell pepper, carrots, onions and jalapenos in large chunks.
Put in a saucepan and cover with cold water.
Heat until the water comes to a boil. (Canned jalapenos don't need to be parboiled.) Process vegetables in a blender (this is too liquid for the food processor) until well blended.
Add 3 cans stewed tomatoes to blender.
Chop other tomatoes by hand for texture. Fill sterilized pint jars and seal.
Use a water bath for 20 minutes.

title: pentecostal potluck casserole
directions: Press ground beef into bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Layer vegetables.
Sprinkle Lawry's seasoning over vegetables.
Top with soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate and shortening melt.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat until lukewarm (120°).
Stir in the vanilla.
Continue beating until a smooth spreading consistency.

title: tortilla cheese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Heat on the stove with a double boiler to avoid scorching or heat in a microwave, stirring every 1 to 2 minutes. Serve in bowls. Garnish with shredded cheese, broken chips and
sour cream, if desired.

title: marinated mozzarella
directions: Slice cheese into slices, 1/4 inch or less.
Add chopped herbs to taste.
Layer cheese with herbs and drizzle each layer with olive oil.
Marinate at least 24 hours.
Good is you can use container which will flip for good olive oil coverage.

title: mom's blueberry pie filling
directions: Mix sugar or honey, cornstarch and salt together.
Add water and 1 cup of blueberries.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and fold in 3 more cups of blueberries.
Pour blueberry mix into pie shell.
Chill for a while until nice and cold.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: three layer raisin pie
directions: Chop raisins; add sour cream, eggs, sugar, spices and salt. Stir well.
Bring these ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat and stir constantly until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and lemon juice.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Whip the cream and fold into cheese mixture. Spread half of cheese mixture into a baked pie shell.
Add the raisin mixture.
Top with remaining cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a rolling boil.
Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Stir until thick and creamy.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chili con carne
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef in heavy skillet (no fat added). Add onion and green pepper; cook until almost tender.
Add tomatoes, seasonings, kidney beans and bean liquid.
Cover and simmer gently about 2 hours.
Remove bay leaves.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: crab cakes
directions: Remove the crusts from the bread; break into small pieces.
Mix well with the egg which has been well beaten.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into cakes, dip into cracker crumbs and saute quickly in small amount of hot fat.
Makes 6 crab cakes.

title: shrimp and crabmeat  delight(serves 10)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients and place in casserole.
Cover with grated cheese.
Top with crushed chips. Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer shredded lettuce and cover with peas.
Mix small sour cream with mayonnaise and sugar to taste.
Add milk to make right consistency to pour over peas.
Next, layer the bacon bits over the dressing.
Spread shredded cheese over bacon bits.
One-half hour before serving, layer 2 cans on fried onions and top with cheese.
You can squeeze boiled sliced eggs around dish if desired.
Also put green onions if you desire.

title: pasta and spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Discard all but 1/4 cup of bacon fat.
Add butter to fat in skillet.
Heat.
Saute onions and pepper until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove sauce from heat.
Cook and drain pasta.
Return to kettle.
Add mushrooms and spinach.
Add sauce and toss over moderate heat until sauce is absorbed and spinach is wilted.
Top with grated cheese and bacon.

title: salmon surprise
directions: Add enough milk to salmon liquid to make 1 1/3 cups.
Add butter to liquid mix and heat.
Mix together salmon, lemon juice and onion.
Add crackers and mix together well.
Put into ungreased casserole dish and pour liquid over the top.
Punch with fork so liquid gets into the salmon mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans.
In mixer bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Add oil and bananas.
Beat on low speed until combined. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes on medium.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan in the oven.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over melted butter, arrange pineapple slices on top of brown sugar, put a cherry in the center of each pineapple slice.
Mix cake as directed on the label using water and eggs (do not use pineapple juice for water).
Beat cake mix as directed.
Pour batter over pineapple and cherries. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Let stand for 5 minutes for topping to begin to set. Then turn upside-down onto a large platter or a cookie sheet. Serve warm, serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool in refrigerator while you mix remaining ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute onion in some bacon fat until soft; add to macaroni.
Add tomato soup.
Saute ground beef and add to mixture.
Season to taste. Serves about 6.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Pour thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Mix well.
Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.
This casserole freezes well after baking and reheats easily in microwave.

title: janet's pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans. Mix at medium speed. Add pecans; hand mix. Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife will come out clean when inserted into pie.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Fry in heavy skillet in oil or bacon grease.
Turn with tongs, until golden brown.
Drain well; don't stack.

title: finger-lickin good dessert
directions: Take angel food cake, tear half of cake into pieces.
Put one layer pineapple over pieces of cake.
Put half of glaze on top. Then mix Cool Whip with cream cheese.
Then add to dessert.
Take rest of glaze last and drizzle over top of cake.

title: any fruit filling strudel
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator for about 3 hours or longer.
Divide dough in 3 portions.
Take one out to work with and place the two remaining portions in the refrigerator to keep cold.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and butter in small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water in a warmed bowl.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 5 cups flour.
Attach bowl and dough hook; mix 2 minutes on speed 2.
Continue beating.
Add remaining flour 1/2 cup at a time until dough clings to hook, about 2 minutes.
Knead and place in greased bowl.
Grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Make cinnamon rolls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak crumbs in milk.
Add remaining ingredients except sauce. Mix well.
Make a loaf and bake in a shallow pan at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Score top of loaf with spoon handle and fill with chili sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all.
Shape into log or ball.
Roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate.

title: quick 'n hearty vegetable barley soup
directions: In a large soup pot brown 1/2 pound ground beef made into meatballs.
Add onions, garlic and the other 1/2 pound ground beef.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except frozen vegetables.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen vegetables.
Cook about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Additional water may be added if soup becomes too thick upon standing.
Yield:
16 (1-cup) servings.

title: miss sandra's banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Bake for 40-45 minutes or until done in large loaf pan.

title: potato casserole au gratin(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets or until almost tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and let cool.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan. Stir in flour.
Slowly add chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and is bubbly.
Stir in half and half, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Remove from heat; cover and let cool.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Combine with celery, onion, pimientos, cheese, melted butter and remaining salt.
Stir in sour cream, then fold sauce into grated potato mixture.
Turn into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs. (Casserole can be refrigerated at this point, if desired.)
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together hash browns, cream cheese, milk and chicken soup. Add onion if desired.
Salt to taste.
Pour into baking dish.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cover chicken with water and add salt, pepper and onion. Simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Crumb the flour, salt and butter.
Mix egg and milk and add gradually to flour mixture until it forms a soft but not sticky dough.
Finish mixing with hands.
Place dough on floured board.
Roll out to 1/16-inch thickness or thicker, if desired.
Cut into 2 inch squares.
Bring broth to a boil and add parsley and potatoes cut into squares.
Add the dough squares gradually and stir often. Keep broth boiling while adding dough to avoid sticking together. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
If there is room in the pot, you can add the chicken or heat it separately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Place in casserole dish in order listed.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Stir after approximately 45 minutes in oven.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream 1 cup butter and 1 cup sugar; add spices and cocoa, then jam and milk.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Cook in layer pans in 325° oven about 45 minutes.
Frost.

title: mustard poultice
directions: Put on a cloth,
then
another cloth on top so it won't blister.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter. Saut onions. Add rest of ingredients and bake until broccoli is done, about 45 minutes, at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted butter.
Press into a 9 inch pie plate.

title: all-american pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and mace. Stir well. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in extracts. Pour batter into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool completely on a wire rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar. Garnish with strawberries or blueberries.

title: stir-fried rice
directions: Stir-fry the onion, pepper and garlic in the bouillon until tender.
Add all the other ingredients; cook until hot.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Pour can of Veg-All over chicken. Dissolve bouillon cube in broth.
Stir in soup.
Mix until smooth and pour on top of Veg-All.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Use 2 tablespoons syrup to 1 cup milk for chocolate milk.

title: lyn's frito salad
directions: Drain beans.
Cut broccoli into flowerets; discard any stems. Mix together beans, onions and broccoli.
Soak overnight in enough dressing to cover mixture.
Just before serving, add tomato, cheese and Fritos.
Add remainder of dressing to taste.

title: peanut butter rice krispie treats
directions: Boil white syrup, sugar and peanut butter 3 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pour into greased cake pan.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In large pan, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain; reserve liquid and set vegetables aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, brown sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda together.
Mix wet and dry ingredients until moist, then add apples and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix all ingredients together, chopping green onions and dried beef real fine.
Leave a little beef to roll cheese ball in.
Also add a few chopped nuts to roll, if you like.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Spread rhubarb in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream sugar and margarine and add milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into batter.
Pour over rhubarb.
Sift together cornstarch and sugar.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cajun cashews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a jelly roll pan with a sheet of foil.
Place the butter, vinegar, Tabasco, cayenne pepper, garlic salt and salt in a medium-sized saucepan over medium heat and stir until the butter and seasonings are well incorporated.
Add cashews and toss until they are well coated with mixture.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on package.
Add fruit and let set up. Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla and spread on the set jello.
Top with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: pork - apple - kraut
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from pork chops.
If 1/2-inch thick, cut chops in half.
Brown meat in skillet on all sides; remove to a casserole.
Add a dash of pepper on each piece.
Drain sauerkraut and rinse quickly with cold water, then place in skillet and stir around to absorb the meat drippings for flavor.
Wash and core the apples, but leave the skin on.
Cut into rings approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Layer in casserole the pork, sauerkraut and top with apple rings.
Sprinkle each apple lightly with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover and bake about 1 hour.

title: crab filled mushrooms
directions: Steam mushroom caps for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Pat dry.
Flake crab meat, combine with last 6 ingredients, fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place on baking dish.
At this point you can cover and chill up to 24 hours or bake in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries and grind in food processor. Add crushed pineapple (drained), salt, pecans, mayonnaise and sugar. Beat Dream Whip according to directions. Fold into cranberry mixture. Add marshmallows and refrigerate for short time.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and blend entire mixture. Spread in an 11 x 15-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread apples in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to top.
Bake 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and flavors.
Make paste of cocoa and food coloring; add to first mixture.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl; add to batter and blend.
Bake in 3 (9 or 10-inch) pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Let cool completely.
Cover with frosting.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa powder and butter in heavy pot.
Cook until it reaches soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Take off heat and add other ingredients.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix eggs, sugar, brown sugar and margarine until creamy.
Then add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add chocolate chips and mix well.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin, baking powder, spice and flour together. Pour on a greased and floured cookie sheet. Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on batter. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Let cool. Combine cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar together. Spread on cake. Roll up and chill until served.

title: meat loaf - italian style
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Add cubed cheese and mix well.
Pack into an 8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch pan or shape into a loaf in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Push all cheese cubes into loaf.
Bake in 350° oven about an hour or until done.
Remove from oven and spread top with catsup.
Return to oven for 5 minutes. This can be served hot or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: day ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash with remaining ingredients until smooth and fluffy.
Put into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Cover and place in refrigerator.
Will keep from 4 to 14 days. Four hours before serving, remove from refrigerator and let come to room temperature.
Sprinkle top with butter and paprika and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until transparent.
Mix all other ingredients with the onions in a casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 10.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Whip potatoes after removing skins with ingredients. Can be frozen at this point. (DO NOT FREEZE TOPPING.)

title: honey glaze for pork roast
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
During last 45 minutes of cooking time, brush pork roast with glaze.
Reserve remaining glaze to serve with roast.

title: yum-yum cake(sugar-free)
directions: Break apart cake into small bits and layer in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour pineapple over cake.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice; chill until ready to serve. Put ice cream in punch bowl; add ginger ale and other mixture and serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread blueberries in pan.
Spread pineapple on blueberries. Spread cake mix, then pineapple.
Melt butter and place on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: paper cup salad
directions: Mix and spoon into paper baking liners for cupcakes.
Leave in metal muffin pan until frozen.
Makes 16.

title: mom's nutritious cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and tomato soup.
Add flour and spices.
Mix well and add nuts and raisins.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in loaf pan at 350°.

title: sparerib sauce
directions: Blend all together with a whisk.
Recipe can be doubled or tripled.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: no-cook peanut butter balls
directions: Measure peanut butter and Karo or honey into bowl and mix. Add dry milk and mix thoroughly.
May need to use hands.
Form into balls about the size of walnuts. Roll in powdered sugar or melted chocolate bits.
Very nutritious candy.

title: rice pudding
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in milk, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in rice and raisins, if desired.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated
325° oven for 35 minutes.
Gently stir rice up from bottom of dish. Continue baking until knife comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg, if desired.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugars, eggs, vanilla and baking soda together.
Add pudding (dry).
Add flour and chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: In large, ovenproof skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Remove from skillet and pour off drippings, leaving 1 tablespoon in pan.
Add onion, green pepper, green onions, garlic and parsley and saute until tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add ham and a little drippings and saute until browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove ham.
Add sausages and brown lightly on both sides, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove.
Add rice to skillet and saute until golden, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in vegetables and arrange chicken, ham and sausage on top.

title: sweet and sour cocktail meatballs
directions: Roll into small balls and drop into salted water or bouillon broth.
Boil slowly for 25 minutes.
Place in sauce.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Crush butterfingers. Mix milk and Cool Whip, then add Butterfingers. Pour in freezer and freeze.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Sprinkle top with crushed Fritos. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo cookie pudding
directions: Put cookies in plastic bag and crush.
Mix together with electric mixer the butter, powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, mix together the milk and pudding.
Now, mix these two together.

title: fish batter
directions: Prepare ham for baking as usual.
Put in a deep roasting pan with 5 cups of water. Put lid on pan.
Heat oven to 500°. Put ham in oven for 15 minutes.
Cut oven off; leave ham in oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Turn oven to 500° again for 15 minutes.
Turn oven off. Leave closed 7 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute sausage. Add other ingredients. Cook, stirring often. May add water chestnuts if desired.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix ingredients as given; stir and mix well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Combine eggs, cottage cheese, cracker crumbs, chiles, 1/2 cup shredded cheese and turn into 8 x 12-inch greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake 3 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings. Heat undiluted mushroom soup and put spoonful on top of each serving.

title: cheese roll
directions: Soften Velveeta cheese.
Place wax paper on top and bottom of Velveeta cheese.
Roll out pretty thin.
Remove top piece of wax paper.
Cream together the softened cream cheese, garlic salt and onion powder.
Spread on top of Velveeta cheese.
Spread chili peppers on top and roll together.
Refrigerate, then cut into thin slices and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli, onion and butter in frypan until tender.
Do not add water.
Mix soup, rice and cheese.
Mix the 2 mixtures together.
Put in casserole dish and cover with Pepperidge Farm seasoned stuffing mix.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: brandi's bonbons
directions: Cream first five ingredients together.
Blend in coconut. Refrigerate.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in top of double boiler. Roll fondant into balls.
With toothpicks, dip into chocolate and put on foil or wax paper to dry.
Keeps best in fridge.

title: best ever brownies
directions: In a
saucepan	on
low
temperature melt chocolate and butter, stirring
to
blend.
Cool.
Add
sugar
and mix well. Beat in
eggs,
one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 15 x
x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25
to
30 minutes or until done.	Cool.
If desired, frost with chocolate frosting.

title: my grandma's apple pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with Butterscotch Sauce.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese for 10 minutes.
Add powdered sugar and whip 10 minutes more.
Blend in cool whip, peanut butter and vanilla and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into crusts and freeze at least 2 hours.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Brown onions in butter until tender.
Add flour until smooth. Slowly add chicken broth.
I usually add about 1/4 of chicken broth at a time, letting it simmer between additions.
Add mushrooms and cream; simmer for about 1/2 hour, or until mushrooms are tender.
Do not let mixture boil.

title: cocoa base for beverages
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Stir in water and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Use immediately or put into jar.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: scones(recipe from an englishman)
directions: Sift flour and baking powder; mix with margarine.
Add egg and milk; mix.
Add raisins; mix.
Spoon into cupcake cups or greased muffin tins.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 6, depending on size of the cupcake cups.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans with salt, pepper, garlic salt and butter. Meanwhile, in another pan, combine soup, cheese, mushrooms, milk and Lipton soup mix and bring to boil.
Drain beans.
Layer in casserole dish beans, onion rings, sauce.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: low calorie potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until soft, add chopped onions, milk and broth. Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
A low calorie soup for a cold winter evening.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: "pam coat"
directions: Beat until creamy.
Use pastry brush to coat baking pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook puddings together with 3 cups of liquid drained from the fruit.
Add orange juice.
Cool.
Add fruits.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients. Melt the margarine in an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Add the corn mixture and stir gently. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, dump pie filling and pineapple together; mix well.
Pour dry cake mix over top evenly.
Dot top with thin slices of margarine or butter.
May top with nuts and shredded coconut, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until brown.

title: fast cookies
directions: Mix and dry onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage; immerse in boiling salted water.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add beef and pork (do not cook).
Add rice and seasonings; mix well.
Remove 1 cabbage leaf at a time.
Remove large center vein.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling on each leaf.
Roll securely.
Spread 1/2 of sauerkraut in bottom of deep pot.
Set in rolls, flap side down.
Add remaining sauerkraut.
Top with tomato puree.
Add boiling water to cover about 1/2 inch.
Simmer over low heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours until rice is tender.
When serving, put sour cream on top.

title: baked pears
directions: Put pears on bottom of pan.
Put butter on pears.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add 1/2 cup of juice and pour over pears. Put crumbs on top and bake until bubbly.

title: french bread farci
directions: Halve the rolls, lengthwise.
Remove soft centers. Leave shells about 1/4 inch thick. Let centers dry. Crumble to fine consistency and add water, parsley, eggs, mustard, oregano and pepper.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown sausage, hamburger and onion; drain.
Melt oleo and garlic in pan and spread over filling and rolls.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese, seasonings and pasta.
Mix with dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: boeuf estouffade(or french daube)
directions: Place all ingredients in order given in heavy Dutch oven or large casserole with a tight fitting lid.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.	Remove from refrigerator and bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours or until the meat is tender.	Cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery and diced whites of 7 eggs in a bowl.
Mash yolks.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, spices,
vinegar and mustard; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cut Velveeta in cubes; add milk.
Heat over low heat; add chili powder to taste and add chili.

title: cheese and bacon appetizers
directions: Mix and spread on Triscuits.
Broil until melted and bubbly. If using Bac*Os, make ahead so Bac*Os can soften up some.

title: cherry slices
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add dry ingredients and stir.

title: market meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine the tomato sauce, barbecue sauce and sugar in a small saucepan over medium heat. Heat the mixture until it begins to bubble, stirring often, then remove it from the heat.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces and tear tortillas into small pieces. Mix chili soup and salsa together in casserole. Layer meat, tortilla, sauce, and cheeses. Repeat
all layers. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hr.

title: joan's bran muffin mix
directions: Pour boiling water over bran (2 cups) and let stand while assembling other ingredients.
Mix in shortening.
Mix remaining bran, sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour, salt and soda. Combine all ingredients and bake as needed at 400° for 20 minutes. Mixture will keep 6 weeks or more in refrigerator.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cheese delight
directions: Cook ground beef. Add remaining ingredients and simmer. Prepare macaroni; drain. Put half of macaroni in casserole. Add sharp cheese, grated or sliced, on top. Add remaining mixture and top with more cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: roberta's french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla. Add one egg at a time; beat 5 minutes after each with electric mixer.
Do not under beat.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream and grated chocolate.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, oil and egg. Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well with dissolved baking soda. Stir in chocolate chips, walnuts and vanilla.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugars, oil, zucchini, vanilla and then dry ingredients.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: good friday vegetable soup
directions: In a covered 4-quart Dutch oven or pot over medium heat, in hot butter, cook carrots, onions, cabbage, parsley and salt for 20 minutes, stirring.
Add chicken broth, green beans and caraway seed.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover Dutch oven and simmer 15 minutes until vegetables are tender. To serve, place a slice of cheese in bottom of bowl.
Ladle hot soup onto cheese.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and hot water.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add pineapple, cinnamon, cloves, flour and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Use ice pick to punch holes in top of cake while hot. Make glaze and pour over cake while hot.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add unbeaten egg and beat well.
Add applesauce.
Combine all the dry ingredients and sift and mix well.
Bake in 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: linda's microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together in bowl, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook on High for 3:40 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook on High for 1:20 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy. Pour onto buttered foil and quickly spread very thinly.
Cool and break up.

title: george's mushroom bacon quiche
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Put cheese on bottom of pie crust. Add crumbled bacon, then mushrooms.
Mix egg, cream cheese, onion, salt and milk.
Pour over bacon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll each biscuit into a 5 1/2-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Cut each circle in half.
Place 1 apple quarter on each piece of dough.
Moisten edges of dough with water.
Bring ends to center, pinching to seal.
Place dumplings in an 8-inch baking dish.
Repeat process with remaining dough and apples.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Drain and combine vegetables in bowl.
In saucepan, boil sugar and vinegar for 10 minutes.
Add oil and pour over vegetables. Let sit overnight.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in medium microwave bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Stir.
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup whipped topping.
Pour 2 cups of milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with a wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Arrange cookies over pudding mixture.
Spread marshmallow mixture over cookies. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Drizzle with chocolate topping just before serving, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: fiesta spread
directions: Brown beef with next 3 ingredients; drain excess fat. Add next 4 ingredients. Mash in beans. Heat, stirring frequently. Add hot pepper seasoning to taste. Garnish with cheese, sliced black olives, lettuce, tomatoes, etc., if desired. Serve warm with crackers, chips or your favorite dippers. Makes approximately 3 1/2 cups.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add vinegar, mustard and beaten egg. Cook until thick.
Cool.
When cooled slightly, add some Miracle Whip.

title: swiss chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, sour cream, water, oil and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add chocolate morsels and nuts; stir until combined.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cocoa and
salt
thoroughly,
so no lumps of cocoa can be seen.
Add
vanilla
and
boiling water. Stir smooth.
Add soft, not melted, butter
and
stir
or beat until smooth, just stiff enough to
spread.
The
frosting may seem too thin at first, but it
stiffens
as it cools.
(If it should get too thick while spreading, stir
in
a few drops of hot water.) Yields enough to cover
two
or 9-inch) layers generously.

title: canning whole kernel corn
directions: Boil corn-on-the-cob until color changes.
Take out of water, allow to cool and cut off the cob; don't scrape cob.
Place in pint jars, filling jars 3/4 full with water and 1 teaspoon salt. Seal tightly.
(Boiling lids will help sealing.)
Place in canner, build pressure to 5 pounds, cut heat off and allow pressure to drop.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together. Combine dry ingredients and stir to mix. Add vanilla and mix.
Stir again to combine. Pour into buttered cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake is set. Cool before slicing.

title: melba toast snacks
directions: Chop green onions finely. Mix with salad dressing and bacon bits until you like the consistency. Spread on Melba toast crackers and top with sliced cherry tomato.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan.
Pour cherry pie filling into pan.
Add pineapple on top of filling.
Add dry cake mix, pecans, and coconut on top of pineapple.
Melt butter and pour over cake.
Cover with foil.
Bake 350 degrees for 60 minutes or until done.

title: cherry delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, spread the pie filling.
Spread the cake mix over the cherry filling.
Sprinkle the nuts over mix.
Drizzle the margarine over the entire mixture. Bake for 1 hour.

title: iced tea syrup
directions: Boil water, then add tea bags.
Steep about 15 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Add sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Store in a glass jar in refrigerator.
I use 1 cup syrup to 2 quarts water.

title: dandelion jelly
directions: Wash blossoms well and remove stems.
Boil 3 minutes in water and strain.
Add pectin and lemon juice and bring to a rolling boil.
Stir in sugar and boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put ingredients in a 4-quart dish.
Everything is put in dish raw.
Layer potatoes, onions, hamburger meat and red beans.
Then put tomato soup on top.
Cover with a lid and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat at high speed with mixer.

title: overnight caramel strata
directions: Combine sugar, butter and corn syrup in heavy small saucepan. Stir mixture over medium-low heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Bring to boil.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Tilt dish to coat bottom evenly; cool. Arrange 6 bread slices in single layer atop caramel, trimming bread to fit. Create second layer in same fashion.
Whisk milk, eggs and vanilla in bowl to blend.
Pour over bread.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: egg & sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix together eggs, onion, sage and milk until well blended. Fold in cheese
and sausage. Put in greased 2 qt. casserole dish. Bake 40 minutes.

title: california dip
directions: Remove seeds from tomatoes and chop; finely slice olives and scallions.
Add chili peppers.
Add vinegar and oil; season with salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Best served chilled and best made soon before serving.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Grate cucumbers and onion fine. Drain on paper towel.
Mix with cheese and mayonnaise.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a 9x13 glass dish melt butter in oven, sprinkle crumbs over butter and pour sweet milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly. Bake 25-30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool and chill thoroughly. Cut into bars. Store loosely at room temperature.

title: harvest apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla. Mixture will be thick.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan, greased and floured, in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: connie's oven fried chicken
directions: Break the eggs over chicken; add salt and paprika and coat chicken well.
Roll the chicken in flour.
In a baking pan or skillet, melt shortening, heating until very hot.
Place the chicken in shortening.
Bake in a 400° oven until the chicken is golden brown.
Turn the chicken over during baking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: deviled egg sandwiches
directions: Boil eggs in water until done. Drain. Let cool before peeling. Put eggs, one at a time, onto plate and smash with fork until all are finished. Add other ingredients, stirring until well mixed. Spread on bread slices for sandwiches and enjoy.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat together well the first 5 ingredients, then stir in rest. Pour into 10-inch pastry.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Best when served warm.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; pour off water.
Salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish; cover with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until "bubbly". This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: be'chamel sauce (greece, france)
directions: Bring milk to a simmer; add onion, bay leaf and pepper. Simmer for a few minutes.
Strain milk stock.
Return to stove. Melt butter and stir in flour.
Remove milk from stove and stir in the flour-butter mixture.
Continue to simmer, stirring until thick, about 10 minutes.
Add salt.

title: stir-fry
directions: Brown beef in 2 tablespoons oil with celery and onion.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Add frozen vegetables and more soy sauce to taste.
Cook until vegetables are tender, but not mushy.
If desired, add Chinese vegetables, water chestnuts and seasoning packet.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, pumpkin and mixed dry ingredients.
Mix all well.
Add nuts, chocolate chips or raisins.
Mix well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt butter; add soda and set aside.
Combine sugar and Karo syrup in large saucepan.
Let come to rolling boil; add peanuts. Cook on high heat for 7 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
